title: All for One
description: Pocoyo wants to play but Baby Bird is flying up in the sky, Pato and Octopus are helicoptering, Elly is jumping up into outer space and even little Caterpillar transforms into a butterfly and flutters away. Pocoyo feels left out so they get together to help him fly up in the sky along with them.

title: Super Pocoyo
description: Today Pocoyo is Super Pocoyo - a superhero determined to rescue his friends from tight fixes - even when they don't need to be rescued.

title: The Trouble with Larry
description: Petunia invents an imaginary friend to help her always get her way.

title: The Rollinator
description: Chep is so good at moss-marbles, no one wants to play him anymore! No one except Sumush who reveals himself to be a tough competitor. To Chep's disbelief, Sumush keeps on winning. But Lilit and Mush-Mush convince their friend not to give up. Chep decides to play his favourite moss-marble: the Rollinator. The one marble he never risked playing before.

title: Sleepover
description: Bing & Coco are having a sleepover today! They mix up their bedtimes and Bing shows Coco his nightlight Owly. But what will happen when Coco turns all the lights out to show Bing what Amber, one of her Rainbow Fairy Mice, can do?

title: Petunia the Piggy Bank
description: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

title: Blankie
description: It's bedtime and Bing's getting ready for bed. But what will he do when his blankie gets wet in the toilet?

title: The Incredible Shrinking Bears
description: Frustrated that she's too small to reach even the bottom-most berries on a tree, Dibble becomes the tallest member of the team when a strange cloud of magical fog shrinks the Care Bears to miniature size. To save them, she must race against time to get them to a reversal-fog that will return them to their normal size.

title: Return to Care-A-Lot
description: Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot, determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.

title: Rock On
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Mac and Tosh Gopher to build them a home underground. Daffy can't remove rocks from the area fast enough and fails to ask for help.

title: The Amazing Tower
description: Pato is building a tower with colored blocks. Pocoyo wants to play too and Pato lets him have a bucket to build his own tower. But when he runs out, Pocoyo takes the blocks from Pato's tower, knocking it down. They start to argue until Pocoyo comes up with a great idea: to build a tower together.

title: Remember When…
description: Pocoyo want to show his friends a film of all his favourite memories. His friends are bored and a bit miffed when they realise they don't feature in the movie at all. So Pocoyo shows them some more favourite bits, this time featuring Elly, Pato and the others, all in embarrassing, funny, silly fixes. Pocoyo thinks it's hilarious but of course his friends are hurt. So Elly shows her favourite bits: all of her bits show her being beautiful, graceful and strong. Pato doesn't like her bits so he shows his. Again, the others get bored and unhappy. They all argue about who should show clips till Baby Bird brings along a selection of clips of everyone having fun together. Those are the best bits of all!

title: Please and Thank You Song
description: Mei goes around the farm with food for the animals. She offers them some food and the animals say "yes please"

title: Flush Hour
description: The babies learn the purpose of toilets.

title: Some Assembly Required
description: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

title: Music
description: Bing, Sula and Pando are making music with Flop and Amma. Everyone has their own instruments, but they all want the drum. Pando gets to go first, but what will happen when it's time to swap and Sula gets the drum next?

title: Magic Fingers
description: Pocoyo appears with a magician's hat and holding a magic wand. He is going to do magic tricks! To his friends' amazement, he makes his fingers disappear, then his hand and finally his foot. In the end, Caterpillar discovers that it was just a trick.

title: Elly Spots
description: Elly is stricken with a case of the Elly Spots, and Pato and Pocoyo have to forsake their picnic to look after her. Once she is better, she makes it up to them.

title: Toy Party
description: Bing and Hoppity, Pando and Bullabaloo are all having a tea party at Sula and Hippoty's today! But what will happen when Sula gives Bullabaloo more cake than Hoppity, and Bing thinks that's not fair?

title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

title: Volcano
description: On a drive through the mountains, Blippi is nearly hit by a puff of smoke from a volcano vent! Curious about what makes a volcano erupt, Blippi and FETCH fly into the volcano. With some close calls, they watch Maggie the Magma Monster gobble up the floor and play a favorite game - The Floor is Lava!

title: Thomas' Promise
description: When Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the same load to Whiff's Recycling Plant, Thomas suggests they each take half of the load, but Diesel turns it into a race.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Swept Away
description: Pocoyo shows us that tidying can be fun too: a broom can be a horse, a guitar, or even a hockey stick!

title: Pato's Bedtime
description: Pato is getting ready for bed. He is wearing his pajamas and is holding his teddy bear. But Pocoyo is still playing and doesn't let him sleep. In the end, Pocoyo falls asleep too, but he is holding Pato's teddy bear!

title: Nina
description: Weird things are happening to Pato: his hose won't work and his favorite hat seems to have a mind of its own. Pato investigates and finds Nina, a tiny girl dressed in green who lives among the plants with her robot Roberto. Pato, you've made a new friend!

title: Hide & Seek
description: Bing's friends all catch the toilet train before playing hide-and-seek but Bing doesn't need to go. Will Bing need the toilet before the game ends?

title: Big and Small
description: Pocoyo is playing with a remote control that makes things big and small. He turns Pato's tower into a tiny tower, and Loula's bone and Elly's doll into gigantic objects. In the end, seeing how his friends all get upset, Pocoyo turns each thing back to its original size.

title: Water, Water Everywhere
description: Grumpy doesn't believe Funshine's warning that an invisible "Big Blob in the sky" is stealing water from a Whiffle garden -- he has pulled too many practical jokes before. To save the garden and his own credibility, Funshine must discover the truth of the menacing "Big Blob."

title: Nia's Balloon Blunder
description: When a parade balloon Nia is set to deliver flies away, Thomas helps Nia adjust her plans to get it back.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Bedtime
description: It's Pocoyo and Pato's bedtime but Pocoyo isn't tired. Every time Pato is just about to fall asleep, he is disturbed by Pocoyo. Eventually Pocoyo is tired out too and together we help Pato drift off to sleep at last.

title: The Real Number One
description: When Thomas' #1 is covered by paint, he sets out to prove to himself that he is still number one, but when everything starts to go wrong for him, he learns what it really means to be #1.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Pop a Wheelie
description: Thomas and Diesel take a friendly competition too far and put an important delivery rescue at risk as they race across Sodor.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Paint Me a Picture!
description: Pocoyo has decided to paint a portrait. But none of his friends will sit still long enough for him to be able to finish his picture. Pocoyo is sad because he feels like he hasn't managed to do what he set out to do - but looking at his picture with fresh eyes he sees that his picture really does capture the true essence of his friends.

title: Swimming Pool
description: Bing, Sula and Flop are going to the Swimming Pool, but what will they do when they find that there's no water in the pool?

title: Picture This!
description: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

title: Elly's Shoes
description: Elly gets a fancy new pair of dressing up shoes. She loves wearing them so much that she won't take them off, even to go to bed!

title: A Clean Sweep
description: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

title: Mush-Mush the Predictor
description: Mush-Mush can't figure out why his sense foot keeps buzzing like crazy until an earthquake shakes the forest. Mush-Mush is sure he predicted it! Convinced he can now predict the future, Mush-Mush starts making predictions for everyone in Mushton.

title: Rise and Funshine
description: Funshine learns he can be as fearless as one of his super hero comic book characters when the Team falls into a magical sleep. To awaken them, he must transport them in the Cloudseeker to a special place in the Silver Lining - but he has never driven it before, and must learn from a comical "How To Pilot the Cloudseeker" video hosted by Grumpy.

title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!

title: Take Us Out to the Ballgame
description: The Baby Looney Tunes experience their very first big stadium baseball game. Lola's favorite team's star batter gets her undivided attention until Lola's coaching affects the very outcome of the contest.

title: Hide and Surprise!
description: While playing hide and seek with Percy, Diesel accidentally gets stranded on a barge that floats out to sea, where it becomes a group effort to rescue him.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Elly on Ice
description: Pocoyo and Pato are having fun ice-skating. Elly is a great dancer and wants to have a go, but every time she tries she falls over flat on her bottom. Even Whale and Octopus put on a great duet ice-skating routine. Poor Elly is about to give up. But we encourage her to have another go, and Pocoyo and Pato help her to get started. Gradually she gets the hang of it and her confidence increases till she performs an amazing routine and achieves the highest score of the day.

title: An UnbeLEAFable Day
description: While the trains are setting up for the Vicarstown Fall Festival, Thomas is feeling down about the end of summer and the changing weather.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Buff Tuff
description: In this country-inspired music video, Buff the Bat-Truck shows off his strength as he tows the bad guys out of town and lifts the spirits of his fellow Batwheels with his sensitive side, all while protecting the people (and critters) of Gotham.

title: Plunk to the Rescue
description: When Plunk discovers that Cheer and the Bears are working with Robbie to foil Bluster's latest bad scheme, he's eager to help out, even if Robbie objects and Cheer thinks it's best that he sits this mission out.

title: Don't Touch!
description: Pocoyo is left in charge of guarding the beautiful castle Elly has built from blocks. Soon Pocoyo can't resist the temptation to touch the castle, and the whole thing comes tumbling down. How can Pocoyo make it up to Elly?

title: Chicks Dig Me
description: Pocoyo finds three chicks whose parents seem to be missing, so he decides to look after them. But he can't get the unruly chicks to calm down or behave. Good job Pato shows up and manages to tame the three cheeky chicks.

title: Three Cheers for Cheer
description: When hard-working Cheer exhausts her crew running a string of drills to protect a Whiffle orchard from possible emergencies, Share's belly badge accidentally creates two Cheer duplicates. Cheer takes a recreation break, unaware that her clones are working Share and the crew - who think they're the real Cheer - even harder.

title: Camping
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly are preparing to go camping. When night falls they begin to play by scaring each other, but what started as a game becomes much more real as they head to bed and everyone is scared by a mysterious noise. In the morning they laughingly discover that the terrifying noise was just the snores of Sleepy Bird.

title: Win, Lose or Daffy
description: A day playing miniature golf is fun for everyone but Baby Daffy, who believes he must beat everyone else at the game. At the end of the day, all but Daffy are having a good time regardless of how they scored.

title: Magic Box
description: Pocoyo has two magic boxes. He puts a telephone in one of the boxes and closes it. The telephone appears in the other box, as if by magic. He decides to make Pato's ball disappear, as a practical joke, but Pato does not think it is funny at all. Fortunately, the ball appears and the two of them end up playing together.

title: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers
description: The Baby Looney Tunes explore a world of botanic wonder as they search for just the right spot to plant a young lemon tree.

title: Atchoo
description: Bing is so excited to see Sula and eat some of Amma's carroty bagels, but what will happen when he can't stop sneezing and feels all hot?

title: Where's Flop?
description: It's lunchtime! Bing's hungry for carrots. But what happens when Flop pops to the shops and Bing stays at home with Amma and Sula?

title: Bam!
description: Set to his rocking theme song, Bam the Batmobile takes to the streets of Gotham and uses his smarts, leadership skills, and awesome gadgets to fight crime and stop the villainous Legion of Zoom.

title: Crane
description: It's the first day on the job for Kareem the Crane, and he's feeling very nervous. Luckily, Blippi and FETCH are there to lend a helping hand! Working together they help Kareem to do his work. Kareem gains confidence and Blippi learns how cranes help to build a skyscraper!

title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song - Healthy Habits!
description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

title: The Beepers: The Visitor
description: The Beepers find the perfect groove after a new friend shreds a little too hard.

title: Space Mission
description: Pocoyo and Pato are playing with their Martian friend. They build a rocket ship with boxes and pretend that they are navigating through space between planets and stars. At the culmination of the mission, the Martian's parents arrive to tell him that it is time to return to his real home.

title: Angry Alien
description: An angry alien finds his way to Pocoyo's world and declares that he wants to be king. Pocoyo, Elly and Caterpillar are all friendly but the alien just bosses them around and tries to scare them. When the alien tells Pato what to do, Pato finds it rather helpful. This goes against what the alien was expecting. Finally the alien is upset because he's not getting the reaction he wanted. He sobs and sobs. Pocoyo et al are concerned and kind. The alien realizes that he is likable, and if he'd just stop being so angry, he could have fun.

title: Get the Egg Home
description: When an egg blows down into the village, it is Mush-Mush and friends' mission to return it to Mush Mountain. Two problems though: there is a Beetle Boom on and all the beetles try to charge and knock over Mushables, and Lilit has always wanted to see an egg hatch so secretly drags her feet.

title: Disco Fleaver
description: Loula has fleas, so Nina uses her shrink ray to try to get them to leave Loula alone. But it turns out the fleas are in the middle of a massive party. Will our friends get Loula to stop scratching?

title: Mystery Footprints
description: Pocoyo and his friends are learning about the different tracks different feet - and paws - make on the ground. When they see some huge footprints they are scared until they realize that one of them is wearing some rather unusual footwear…

title: Magic Act
description: Pocoyo is doing a magic show. He expects everyone to watch very carefully and take him very seriously but unfortunately his tricks don't quite go to plan and his friends all laugh. They're really enjoying the show. They think Pocoyo is great at being a funny magician. But that's not what Pocoyo wants to be - he wants to be taken very seriously - so he goes off in a huff. In the meantime, Pato, Elly and Baby Bird go around Pocoyo-land to tell everyone about the magnificent hilarious magician whose show they enjoy so much. As Pocoyo sulks, his friends gather around him, excited to see his tricks. Pocoyo is overwhelmed that his friends liked his show so much. He does some more tricks and his friends are thrilled.

title: Swing
description: Bing and Pando are taking turns on the swing. Bing counts to ten, but will Pando do the same?

title: Cake
description: Bing is having a cake party today, and is excited to show Sula the raspberry he decorated the cake with especially for her. But it's hard for Sula to see, so what happens when Bing tilts the cake a little too far?

title: Let's Tidy Up!
description: Pocoyo and Elly are playing and making a mess in Pato's room. At first, Pato doesn't mind, but when he realises that they don't tidy up afterwards he gets very mad. How will he deal with them?

title: Wide Load Vacay: Dumbrella
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, have been traveling on the back of a truck in the rain for days. Charlie produces an umbrella to help his friend but unfortunately it's a "dumbrella" and it's looking to have some fun with them!

title: Melissa the Hero
description: Melissa brags about helping Petunia to the point of self-aggrandizement.

title: Pocoyo Goes to School
description: Caterpillar and Baby Bird are at school. They have backpacks, notebooks and pencils. Elly is the teacher. Pocoyo and Pato don't want to play with them. They would rather play ball. But they gradually come to like what they are doing at school better and end up joining their friends.

title: Magical Watering Can
description: Pocoyo gives the last drop of water from his watering can to his friends instead of using it to water his musical flowers. Pato and Elly are grateful, so they re-pay the favor.

title: Good Vibrations
description: Lilit is under pressure. Truff, the most talented musician in Mushton, has invited her, Mush-Mush and Chep to form a band with him. Only problem is they can hardly play music! Truff insists: they just need to relax and feel the groove. But when Truff tells his new band they will perform at the Food Snail, Lilit isn't relaxed at all!

title: Things That Go Bugs in the Night
description: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

title: House
description: Bing is playing "Big Bad Wolf" today with Sula, Coco and Charlie and Bing gets to be the wolf! But what will happen when Bing wants to come into the brick house with everyone else?

title: The Tattletale
description: Lola begins tattling on the other babies until her friends no longer want to play with her.

title: Do You Speak Dance/A New Spider in Town/Dollhouse Mates
description: "Maizie" keeps ignoring Lucas and Findley, but not only do they learn she has a cousin, they also learn a new skill!/ Lucas befriends a bright purple toy spider, and Findley gets jealous./ Lucas and Findley move into the dollhouse together.

title: Counting Cows
description: When Thomas and Percy volunteer to deliver a herd of cows, they realize that the cows keep wandering off on their own adventures unless the two friends can both pay better attention.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Lost
description: Bing and Flop are in the park with Hoppity. What will happen when Bing finds some dog poo?

title: Parking Lot
description: Bing's parking his speedy cars but what will Bing do when Charlie wants to play too?

title: Fancy Dress Party
description: There is a fancy dress party and competition and Pato is absolutely convinced that he will win. But when he has to choose a costume, he puts so much pressure on himself that he ends up not even going to the party. Will Elly and Pocoyo be able to change his mind?

title: Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind
description: Tweety feels neglected when no one wants him on their museum scavenger hunt team. Using his innate sleuthing abilities and the help of a friendly museum guard, Tweety proves to be the best scavenger hunter of them all. Once Tweety wins the contest, everyone wants him on their team.

title: Calling All Batwheels
description: A music video introducing all of Batman's heroic vehicle squad - the Batwheels - showcasing their incredible gadgets, stunning talents, and unique personalities.

title: A Present for Elly
description: Pocoyo decides to make a very special birthday present for Elly. Can you guess what it is?

title: Sleepy Bird's Surprise
description: Sleepy Bird's egg takes on a life of its own. Pocoyo and Pato have to get it back to the nest - just in time for it to hatch.

title: Pocoyo Recycles
description: Pocoyo and Pato find some recycling containers. Elly appears with lots of things to recycle: bottles, cans and newspapers. Fred also has things to recycle, but Pocoyo and Pato will have to convince him that it is a good idea.

title: There's Nothing Like a Good Book
description: A nagging question regarding the composition of the moon brings the Baby Looney Tunes to experience their very first visit to the library.

title: Pato's Phone
description: Pato is hooked on his phone and Pocoyo and Elly become worried because he doesn't even want to play with them anymore. They will try everything they can to get their friend back. Will they succeed?

title: The Great Race
description: Elly and Pocoyo have a race, and are surprised when an outsider narrowly beats them.

title: Snow Day
description: The babies experience their first snowfall.

title: A Very Special Guest
description: It's Christmas and Pocoyo and friends are preparing to celebrate at Elly's house. Elly, Pato, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are in charge of decorations and dinner, while Pocoyo and Loula fetch a tree. Everything is going well until Pocoyo and Loula bring the tree, along with an unexpected guest: a huge yeti! Elly, Pato, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are very scared, so Pocoyo will have to show them that there is always space for one more at the table for Christmas dinner. Will they be able to enjoy it?

title: Bruce Bunny
description: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce.

title: Let It Bee
description: Wanting to rush off to climb Mush Mountain, Mush-Mush is in a hurry checking nectar level in flowers - a job that takes time and care. Soon Mush-Mush's haste causes disaster when he scares all the bees away. Now Mush-Mush and friends have to find a way to lure the bees back…

title: Party Time
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly are organizing a birthday party. Fred wants to help them, so Pocoyo asks him to blow up balloons. Poor Fred is having a bit of a hard time, but in the end he gets a pleasant surprise: the birthday party they were organizing was for him!

title: Letting Off Steam
description: When Thomas and Percy get into their first big fight they're afraid that their friendship is over... until Nia helps them figure out how to resolve it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Inventions
description: Pocoyo and Nina create some mad inventions to finish their chores quickly so they can go to a party. But things are never that simple. Will they be able to make it?

title: Lonesome Lucas/I Can't See You/Don't Eat Me
description: Lucas wakes up in the middle of the night. How long can a night alone last?/ Lucas tries to beat Bodhi at Hide and Seek./ When Findley watches a show about spiders eating flies, he thinks Lucas wants to eat him!

title: Like a Duck to Water
description: Daffy overcomes his fear of the swimming pool.

title: Talent Show
description: It's the day of the Talent Show. First Elly does some ballet karate. Then it's Baby Bird's turn: he's a crazy pinball wizard. Caterpillar nervously says she'll have her go later. Whale sings down the line from underwater. Pato does some unbelievable impersonations. Pocoyo reads out a story he's written. It's Caterpillar's turn but she's too scared. She doesn't want to do her bit. She's shy. We persuade her to show us her talent. She does a talk all about hippopotami. Once she's started, there's no stopping her. It's wonderful. What a fantastic and unforgettable display of unique talents. Everyone can do something special.

title: Art
description: The characters have prepared an exhibit that displays different art genres, such as painting, sculpture and photography. Pato plays the role of art critic and visits the exhibit, but there is nothing he likes there. The rest of the characters ask him to show his artistic skills and then Pato realizes that making art is not so easy.

title: Fishing
description: Pocoyo and Pato are fishing. They have a net and a fishing rod with a strange hook: Caterpillar. They throw in their line and wait. Caterpillar reaches the bottom of the sea and becomes friends with a fish. Pocoyo and Pato don't manage to catch anything and have to go down to the bottom of the sea to find out what is going on.

title: Meet the Batwheels
description: An action-packed music video of the Batwheels' most exciting adventures set to an extended version of the series' theme song.

title: Crazy Inventions
description: Pocoyo the super inventor has a lab full of hare-brained inventions. His helper Pato volunteers to test out his new time machine, but things don't go quite to plan and Pocoyo will travel through the third dimension to rescue his friend.

title: Oh My Compost
description: When Sushi-Mushi breaks the only spoon he has ever cooked with, he declares his cooking days are over! So Mush-Mush and friends step up to cook for everyone instead. How hard can it be? It turns out, very! The Mushlers will have to convince Sushi-Mushi he's still the best compost chef, even without his favorite spoon!

title: Dirty Dog
description: Pato is enjoying watering his flowers when all of a sudden he notices that something smells horrible. It's Loula: she stinks. Elly is putting on perfume, and she too notices how bad Loula smells. Pooey! When Pocoyo can't eat his sandwich because Loula smells so bad, he makes a plan. Loula needs a wash. The only problem is, Loula doesn't want to get in the bath and gives chase to Pocoyo, Elly and Pato. Pocoyo and his friends decide to trick Loula into a cleaning machine but their plan is thwarted. However will they stop the smell? Then, all of a sudden it begins to rain and Loula finally gets her long-awaited clean.

title: Baby-Gate
description: Melissa spreads rumors about the babies, and Bugs goes undercover to find the truth.

title: Mind Your Manners
description: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny.

title: Cinema
description: Pato is going to show a movie for his friends, who will be the audience. He shows us the screen, the seats and the projector. Everything is going well until the film gets jammed and the audience laughs. Pato gets angry but his friends manage to get him to sit down and enjoy the show with them.

title: The Big Freeze
description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself.

title: Ice Cream
description: It's hot out and Bing and Flop are trying to catch up to Gilly to get some ice cream! Bing finally catches up with Gilly and gets his yummy delicious carroty ice cream. Does he drop his ice cream as he waves goodbye?

title: Drummer Boy
description: Pocoyo wants to drum, but his friends are all busy playing different things. Pocoyo learns that sometimes his friends don't want to do exactly the same things as him.

title: Watch the Storm
description: When Chep asks Mush-Mush and Lilit to go storm-watching and they refuse, Lilit feels bad and convinces Mush-Mush to join their friend. But there are no storms on the horizon. When they notice Chanterelle going through the forest mysteriously, our Mushlers decide to find out what she's up to instead. That's when a big storm starts brewing on the horizon.

title: House Flies Don't Dance/Flying the Nest/The Insult
description: Lucas and Maizie help Findley learn to dance./ Arlo believes he's a big owl now, so it's time to fly his nest. But is Arlo ready to leave his friends behind?/ When Lucas calls Findley a mean name, he tries to make things right again.

title: Playtime
description: Pocoyo shows up with a box full of toys: building blocks, a puzzle and a ball. His friends want to play with him, but Pocoyo won't let them because he would rather play alone. At the end of the episode he realizes it is more fun to play with friends and decides to ask his friends' forgiveness and asks them to play with him.

title: Christmas in July
description: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

title: The Super-Long Shortcut
description: When Gordon is unable to make an important delivery on his own, Thomas offers his help, but Gordon insists on second-guessing Thomas's every move.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Dandelion
description: Bing finds a dandelion in the park and loves blowing the seeds and watching them fly away! He decides to save the last one to give it to Sula, but will he be able to keep the seeds from blowing away in the wind as he takes it to her?

title: Get Active Dance
description: Mei, Ella, animals and vegetables have a farm active day exercising and organising the farm

title: The Grand Final
description: When Elly and Pato see what a bad basketball player Pocoyo is, they decide not to play with him. Pocoyo is angry if he can't play neither will his friends! He boycotts the game in crazy and funny ways. How will it all end?

title: A Wish-Full Reunion
description: Mysterious flying hearts appear in Care-A-Lot and bring Wish Bear to the Silver Lining. She joins the Care Bears on a mission to bring a mystical mother bird's missing baby chicks home, and give a new home to an orphan bird.

title: Stuck
description: Bing & Sula are climbing on trees in the Howly Woods today, and it's tricky-hard! Sula needs Bing's help to climb up, and get back down again. But what will happen when Bing wants to climb up even higher?

title: Pocoyo Gets it Right
description: Pocoyo wants to play 'pitch and putt' like his friends, Pocoyo and Elly, but he can't quite get the hang of it. He watches carefully and finally grasps where he was going wrong.

title: The Best Bedroom
description: Elly's bedroom has a bed and a closet full of clothes. Pato's room has a bedside table and a lamp. Pocoyo's is full of toys. All three think they have the best bedroom but which of the three is really best?

title: Backwards Day
description: It's Backwards Day! But Thomas misunderstands the game and accidentally delivers the wrong cargo to the wrong places.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Rock is a Hard Place
description: Pocoyo and his friends have a rock band and Fred the Octopus has organized a photo shoot. They can't decide on the front man. They're about to perform for their fans. Will they be able to come together as a group?

title: Lunchbox
description: It's lunchtime! Bing shows Pando and Sula his brand new Hoppity Voosh lunchbox! And Pando has the exact same one MATCH! But then they mix their lunchboxes up.

title: Picnic
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly go on a picnic. Soon the sandwiches they have in their basket begin to move all by themselves and escape. The three friends pursue the sandwiches until they are finally able to trap them. At the end of the episode Pocoyo, using a magnifying glass, discovers that ants were attempting to take the sandwiches and invites them to the picnic.

title: Having a Ball
description: Pocoyo and Pato are enjoying playing with their new ball. But all of a sudden, the ball takes on a life of its own, and Pocoyo and Pato have to chase it. Who's got the ball…? It's Baby Bird who just wants to play too!

title: Monsterplant
description: Bluster creates a mad scientist's monster from a clump of moss and sends it to scare the Whiffles away. The kindhearted Monsterplant just wants to be friends with them, but the Whiffles are frightened away by how he looks. Share and Dibble work together to show the Whiffles how nice Monsterplant is on the inside.

title: Musical Statues
description: Bing gets to choose the game at Amma's Creche, but will his also be the winner?

title: The Silly Little song
description: The other children and the animals all get together to cheer Rishi up with a funny, silly song.

title: Cooking with Elly
description: Elly is in the kitchen. She is wearing an apron because she has just finished making a birthday cake for Caterpillar. Suddenly, Pocoyo and Pato show up and somehow the cake ends up on the floor. The three of them make another cake together and set the table to give Caterpillar a surprise. In the end, they will also get a surprise.

title: Whistle Woes
description: When Thomas's whistle suddenly stops working, he learns that he doesn't need his whistle to still be himself.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Insert Coin
description: The grumpy Martian is back in Pocoyo's white world and he's kidnapped Elly's doll. Surprise surprise! Elly asks Pocoyo for help and he turns the rescue mission into a video game, complete with a final monster. It's not that hard to ask for things politely. "Please" can get you a long way.

title: Hack Attack
description: Nina doesn't like football, so she goes off to find a different game. Meanwhile, Roberto stands in as goalkeeper but after he gets hit with the ball one too many times, his circuits break down and he goes crazy. Quick! Someone fix Roberto!

title: Let's Go Camping!
description: A camping trip is planned - but Pocoyo and Pato have too much luggage. In the end they realize that all you really need for a nice camping trip are your friends - and then it doesn't really matter whether you're at home or away.

title: Cock-A-Doodle-Doo-It!
description: On their first farm visit, the Baby Looney Tunes meet a young, dispirited rooster named Baby Foghorn Leghorn. They work together to build his self-confidence, unleashing powers of persuasion and elocution that even Foghorn never knew he had.

title: Cross That Bridge/Knock Knock! Who's There?
description: The train needs to cross the ravine, which becomes difficult when the Martians accidentally break the bridge./The Zee Mobile is great at counting the chickens at the farm, but won't stop crashing into and ruining MacBarm's barn door.

title: Never Say Try
description: Sylvester is a bad dancer and finger painter so he believes he'll never be good at anything.

title: Ducks
description: Bing and Sula are feeding the ducks in the park, but will Bing remember to stand statue still?

title: Baby Brouhaha
description: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

title: Shutterbug
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird are bored of Pato's countless flower photos so they encourage him to take pictures of them instead. But each time Pato takes a photo, someone moves. Pato is exasperated because he wants to take perfect portraits but there's always something not quite right. Pato gives up. His friends put on an exhibition of his photos to show him that his pictures may not be exactly what he had in mind, but they really are wonderful because they capture the fun the friends have together.

title: Muck Struck
description: Environmental disaster: the water is polluted! Elly can't make her tea and Pato can't water his plants. What's up? The three of them decide to clean out the lake to get the water back to its crystal clear state.

title: Flying/Dr. Lucas is in the House/Arlo's Portrait
description: After watching Findley in flight, Lucas wonders what it would be like to fly./ Dr. Lucas tries to make all his friends feel better but ends up under the weather himself./ Lucas decides to paint a portrait of Arlo. But Arlo can't sit still.

title: Painting with Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo and his friends are painting a fruit still life. Pato is painting with a brush, Elly with pencils and Pocoyo is using crayons. Baby Bird goes to sit in the still life so that his friends can include him in their drawings. While he is waiting, he keeps eating the fruit, making everyone repeat their drawings. In the end, they have all portrayed the only thing left in the still life: Baby Bird.

title: Not in My Backyard
description: Pocoyo discovers some old rubbish and decides to have a clear out. Baby Bird, Pato and Elly do the same. Soon there's a huge pile of rubbish, and it turns out it's on Caterpillar's doorstep. The rubbish keeps getting thrown around until finally Pocoyo follows the rubbish and realizes it's just going in a circle. In order to break the cycle, Pocoyo helps his friends make some new fun toys and games out of the rubbish.

title: Snow-verload
description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself, just as Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot! They're determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.

title: Grasshopper Chep
description: All the Mushables have fun zooming down a long mudslide except Chep, who just can't get up the courage to do it. But when Fung and Miff tease him for being scared, he promises that he will do something that no Mushable has ever done before - ride a grasshopper! Chep is in for the ride of his life!

title: Magic Words
description: Something really weird is happening today... Every time the narrator asks what Pocoyo is playing with, the audience says something else and Pocoyo's object changes. The audience has the power and they're feeling pretty playful!

title: I Strain
description: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

title: Pocoyo's Band
description: Pocoyo finds a box full of musical instruments. When he learns how to use them, he calls on his friends to form a rock band. At first the band is a disaster, but in the end they learn to play together and are able to make some great music.

title: Choosing
description: Bing and Flop are at Padget's shop today choosing a toy to buy. And it's tricky hard to pick just one! And what will happen when Bing thinks he has made the wrong choice and wants to swap?

title: Ocean
description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

title: Space Christmas
description: It's Christmas and Angry Alien, who hates this holiday, is preparing to spend the evening all by himself, with no celebrations... until Pocoyo and friends turn up at his house to keep him company. How is he going to like Christmas with no decorations, carols or friends? But they're here to solve that! Angry Alien will try everything he can to stop them from making this a great Christmas. Will he succeed?

title: Pato's Postal Service
description: When Pocoyo wants to send a letter to Elly, Pato embraces the very important role of postman. After much to-ing and fro-ing, Pato delivers a mammoth package!

title: The Perfect Fritter
description: Chep has been watching Sushi-Mushi test new compost fritters recipes. When Mush-Mush gets to taste one, he can't believe it: Sushi-Mushi has cooked the perfect fritter. He tells the news to everyone in Mushton and now, all the Mushables want to taste the perfect fritter too! Only problem is the pressure is so high Sushi-Mushi can't remember the recipe anymore.

title: Face Painting
description: Pocoyo and Pato are drawing pictures, and Elly wants them to draw her new doll. So they draw a picture of the eyes, another of the nose, another of the mouth and two drawings of the ears. To keep Elly from getting angry, they decide to put together a giant picture with all the parts of the doll.

title: Pocoyo's Friend
description: The arrival of Pocoyo's invisible friend creates problems with Pato and Elly. Since they can't see him, they are left out of the games! Will the kids learn to play together?

title: Vamoosh on the Loosh
description: Pocoyo promises to teach Baby Bird to drive the Vamoosh but keeps putting it off. Fed up, Baby Bird decides to have a go on his own but he doesn't know how. The Vamoosh spins out of control. Pocoyo realises he must keep to his promise and teach Baby Bird to drive properly.

title: Jumping Pal/ Trouble at the Top/ Avocado's Fan
description: Lucas encounters a peculiar creature - A Jumping Bean. / When Findley and Avocado get shut in the attic, the stuck duo embrace the moment! / Arlo is starstruck by Avocado's popularity and becomes her biggest fan.

title: Baby Bird Bother
description: Baby Bird is in awe of Pocoyo as he plays skillfully with a bouncy ball. Baby Bird continues to admire Pocoyo but this time it's his construction skills as Pocoyo plays with his blocks. And yes, Baby Bird thinks Pocoyo is the best at painting too. At first Pocoyo thinks it's great to have an admirer but soon, Pocoyo can't do anything without Baby Bird interrupting. Eventually Pocoyo gets so frustrated that he sends Baby Bird away. Pocoyo enjoys doing everything all by himself but it's not long before he wonders where his friend Baby Bird has gone. When Pocoyo realizes that Baby Bird was only trying to be his friend Pocoyo decides to invite Baby Bird to a party especially for him.

title: Elly's Big Chase
description: Elly inadvertently sets off on a fantastic journey - all the while fast asleep on her chair - as Pocoyo and Pato protect her from danger.

title: Spin Out
description: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy.

title: An Almost Eggless Easter
description: When the Easter Bunny's beautifully-painted eggs are drained of their color, it looks like Dibble will miss her first Easter egg hunt - she's really been looking forward to it. The Bears must find a way to repaint all the eggs before the big day.

title: Wrong!
description: On an orchard outing, picking bushels of fresh apples for Granny's home-baked pies, the Baby Looney Tunes encounter Melissa, who is in a mood to tell everyone that her method of apple picking is the only way.

title: Great Shot!
description: Pocoyo and Nina are playing tennis until Pato switches the tennis ball for a basketball ball. Elly joins in and adds rugby rules. A straightforward tennis match has turned into a nonsensical combination of sports!

title: Flower Power
description: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden.

title: Unlock the Magic: The Beginning
description: The discovery of an ancient, lost gateway leads the Care Bears on a rescue mission in the Silver Lining, a realm of natural wonders and comical creatures in the clouds beyond the borders of Care-A-Lot. While there, new discoveries expand the mission, challenging Cheer, Grumpy, and the mission team to grow beyond their present abilities and help the denizens of the Silver Lining.

title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?
description: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure.

title: Daffy Did It!
description: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying.

title: Fruit & Vegetables
description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

title: Dibble's Dust-Up
description: Grumpy's determination to get the Cloudseeker clean is comically thwarted when Dibble befriends a stowaway trio of cute dust bunnies.

title: Save Our Cinnamon
description: Granny's sister's beloved bakery, Cakery Bakery Dock, home of her wonderful trademark cinnamon rolls, is being put out of business so her landlord can tear down the bakery to build a parking lot. This galvanizes the Baby Looney Tunes to work together to bake one giant cinnamon roll as a tourist attraction to save the bakery, a project that ends up involving the whole town.

title: Skateboard
description: Bing and Flop are in the park when Pando vooshes past on his skatebaord. Pando agrees to let Bing try out his skateboard. But what happens when Bing comes to a steep hill and the skateboard goes faster and faster?

title: Dressing Up
description: Bing and Coco are dressing up and they both need a crown. What will they do when they see there is only one crown?

title: Cool for Cats
description: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool.

title: What a Stinker
description: Chep is very excited: tonight, a rare and extremely stinky plant is going to bloom! But he already promised Mush-Mush to play their favourite game. When he chooses the flower instead, Mush-Mush is angry and the two friends stop talking. But when Mush-Mush realises that Chep is about to miss the blooming, he decides he won't let that happen and helps his friend!

title: Sylvester the Pester
description: An attention-starved Sylvester won't let Granny have any time to herself.

title: Winter Games
description: Pocoyo is so eager to win a medal in the Winter Games that he forgets about the most important part, having fun! Will he remember what it's all about?

title: The Breathtaking Bolly Show
description: If Mush-Mush had Bolly's speed, he'd want everyone to see just how awesomely fast he was. But Bolly is different - he just likes to use his speed helping Mushables. So when Mush-Mush organizes a big stunt for Bolly, he refuses. He just doesn't like to show off. But Mush-Mush promised everyone a show so a show he will give them with Mush-Mush performing instead of Bolly! Gulp!

title: Happy Place
description: Time to share some of the honey made at Lellobee City Farm with everyone that visits the farm

title: Hula Hoop
description: Coco is showing Bing her new Holly Hula Hoop, but will be Bing be able to hula like Coco?

title: Angry Alien Strikes Back
description: The Angry Alien is back in Pocoyo World with a brilliant master plan: he's going to impersonate Pocoyo! Everything goes smoothly at first, but soon enough everyone starts switching bodies. What is this madness?! (It's so much fun!)

title: Loose Change
description: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change.

title: The Mysterious Seepod
description: Chep has come across a new seedpod specimen. Mushpot warns him not to take it though. But the temptation is too much and Chep can't resist taking the seedpod and opening it to find it is full of itchy powder! Argh! Mush-Mush and Lilit do their best to help their friend, but it seems like the only way Chep can get rid of the itching is to ask Mushpot for a remedy.

title: Who's Eating Mushton
description: Everyone in Mushton is finding that their precious wooden things are being munched and destroyed by someone or something. All the evidence points toward Truff's new woodworm pet Chompski. But Truff refuses to believe Chompski would do such a thing! It's up to Chep, Lilit and Mush-Mush to convince Truff. But first they have to catch Chompski in the act!

title: Cereal Boxing
description: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

title: Festival of Hearts
description: When two greedy gnomes steal Love-a-Lot's gift-making crystal heart, the Care Bears must get it back in time for the Festival of Hearts that they are holding for the Whiffles. In doing so, they have to teach the gnomes the meaning of caring.

title: Time Out!
description: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

title: A Lot Like Lola
description: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her.

title: Big Boots
description: Bing and Sula are being giants and splashing in puddles with their rainy boots. What will happen when Bing finds a big puddle?

title: Chocolate Factory
description: Blippi's love for chocolate makes him wonder "How are chocolate bars made?" They head into a chocolate factory to find out, get a tour from Bard the Chocolate Bar, and FETCH gets a close-up look at the chocolate-making process!

title: Elly's Doll
description: Pocoyo is charged with looking after Elly's favorite doll, but he breaks it. Instead of telling her the truth, he pretends to be the doll. It's only when nature gets the better of Pocoyo that Elly realizes what's going on. She forgives Pocoyo warmly and mends her doll.

title: Lucas and His Friends/The Owl That Said Why/Happy Burpday
description: A series of 6 shorts introducing all of Lucas's friends and ending with a song. / Arlo keeps asking questions! Lucas learns to be more patient. / Lucas discovers a slice of cake and decides to throw a surprise party for Findley.

title: The Great Giggle
description: The Care Bears are to witness the annual blooming of the Pinata Tree, an ancient event that can only happen if the Keeper of the Tree sees something that makes him giggle. Good Luck's giggle-inducing entertainment act goes awry because he relies on his errant lucky shamrock for success. He must learn to forgo luck and practice his act instead.

title: Funshine's Un-fun Day
description: Funshine can't bring himself to tell Cheer he accidentally broke her beloved necklace. His attempts to repair the broken necklace end in failure, so he hides it. When Cheer wrongly thinks Dibble is responsible for the disappearance of the necklace, Funshine knows he must tell her the truth.

title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

title: Mystery Boxcars
description: Kana is upset when she keeps running out of power, but a mystery scavenger hunt is just the thing to cheer her up.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Pastime for Petunia
description: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests.

title: Get Lost Loula
description: Let's play Hide and Seek! Pocoyo is the seeker and is brilliant at it - but only thanks to Loula. When Loula gets all the praise for being a super-seeker, Pocoyo is jealous. He throws a ball very far away to make Loula run off and chase it. His friends think it was a nasty thing to do and so Pocoyo feels bad and decides he must now find Loula. They follow her footprints but she's gone really far and they just can't find her anywhere. Finally at an island in the sea they despair: they think she's gone forever. But we can already see that Loula is safe and sound. Everyone is reunited and Pocoyo can celebrate being a super-seeker too, after all.

title: Giving
description: It's Sula's birthday! Bing is choosing the perfect present for her, but really loves it himself. Will Bing keep the present for himself?

title: Wide Load Vacay: Big City Dancers
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, traveling on the back of a truck visit NYC where the rhythms of the city make Charlie wanna dance his little back porch off. Frank … not so much. But when you go far enough into the city, anything can happen.

title: Talkie Taxi
description: Bing and Sula discover a new toy at Amma's creche - Talkie Taxi. What will they do when they discover the taxi talks a lot?

title: Hole Lotta Trouble
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly are playing marbles: you aim at a hole and shoot. But this isn't a regular hole. It's swallowing everything! It even gobbles up our friends. How are they going to get back home?

title: Giggle Bug
description: When Pocoyo is down in the dumps, Octopus cheers him up. Elly falls over doing her latest dance routine and Octopus cheers her up too. Finally Pato is in a bad mood, and Octopus has to work really hard to get him to giggle.

title: Lights! Camera! Tweety!
description: The Baby Looney Tunes are very eager to visit the local TV station, home of their favorite live children's show. When Floyd accidentally locks them inside the studio moments before airtime, they are forced to put on today's program all by themselves!

title: Guess What?
description: Pocoyo plays a game with us. He shows us a series of different extremely strange shapes and wants us to guess what they are. A fun guessing game, learning to look at things in different ways...

title: The Sandman Is Coming
description: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes.

title: The Day of the Dead
description: Pato misses his Grandfather and decides to honor his memory on Day of the Dead by making a shrine with his photograph and the things he liked the most. Pocoyo and friends will help him to set it up to try cheer up Pato.

title: Who Said That?
description: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it.

title: The Creature from the Chocolate Chip
description: Sylvester eats all of Granny's cookies then makes up a cookie monster to blame.

title: Garbage Truck
description: Blippi and TABBS shrink down and fly into a garbage truck where they meet Horace, a singing and dancing fly, who shows them what he loves to eat--garbage!

title: Call Me
description: Pato has bought a brand new phone and can't get enough of this fantastic technology. But he'll soon realize his flashy new device comes with some drawbacks: he can't hang out with his friends and be on his phone at the same time. Give it a rest, Pato!

title: Sandy Versus the Storm
description: When a big storm approaches, Thomas and company must complete all a week's worth of deliveries by the end-of-the-workday whistle, but when Sandy needs repairs, Thomas and the gang will realize just how important Sandy is to the team!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Voo Voo
description: It's breakfast time, and when Bing accidentally spills his Krispos, Voo Voo can help clean it up. But will that be all Voo Voo cleans up?

title: Flu the Coop
description: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

title: Goodbye, Ghost-Scaring Machine
description: Percy announces he's giving up his Ghost Scaring Machine - he's too old for it now. It soon becomes clear that the machine is good for more than just "scaring ghosts."
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Little Something Between Friends
description: Pocoyo and Pato fall out - really fall out. They are so angry with each other that they build a wall between themselves. They each sit sulking on either side of the wall, until gradually they realize that it's no fun being angry with your friend, and actually they miss each other.

title: Australia Kangaroo
description: Blippi stumbles across a Kangaroo Crossing sign in Australia and wonders "How high can a kangaroo jump?" His new kangaroo mate Rudy is happy to demonstrate, challenging Blippi to a hopping race around the famous sandstone monolith Uluru. Can Blippi jump as high as a kangaroo?

title: Rain, Rain Go Away
description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

title: Keep Going Pocoyo
description: Pato and Elly are enjoying skipping with a skipping rope. Pocoyo thinks it looks like fun and he wants to skip too. Try as he might though, Pocoyo can't do it. So he asks his friends for help.

title: Too Hot to Handle/The Big Squeak/Big Jumping Spider
description: Findley can't resist some freshly baked cookies that are too hot to eat./ Avocado's new toy is driving everyone crazy with its noisy squeaker./ Lucas performs epic jumps all around House./ Findley is nervous and wishes Lucas wouldn't jump.

title: Play Day
description: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

title: Sleeping Dogs/Skunked/Arlo And The Snake
description: Lucas and Findley discover a cake, and they try to keep Avocado asleep so everyone can have some./ Avocado gets skunked. Thankfully, Lucas helps her laugh at the situation./ Lucas has to convince Arlo that the garden hose isn't a snake.

title: Elly's Computer
description: Elly is playing with her computer, which has a screen, a mouse and a keyboard, while Pocoyo waits to play ball with her. Pocoyo gets angry because Elly isn't playing with him, but then Elly finishes her videogame and they can finally go out and play ball together.

title: Mixed Signals
description: The team receives a video message from Tenderheart that their mission has successfully ended and they can return home. Cheer suspects something about the message is wrong, but other members of the team don't agree. Cheer courageously stands her ground and keeps the team together while she solves the mystery, and reveals the message was faked by Bluster.

title: Suprise, It's Spring
description: Puff doesn't like change much. And with spring about to burst forth and all the changes spring brings, he is puffing out nervous fog which is blanketing the whole of Mushton. Mush-Mush and friends need to get Puff to relax and celebrate spring together with all the other Mushables!

title: Scooter Madness
description: Pocoyo and Pato find Elly's scooter and decide to take it back to her. Pato enjoys showing off his scooter skills and quickly forgets who it belongs to. Pato's scooter tricks get bigger and bigger until eventually he breaks the scooter into pieces. Pocoyo and Pato try to fix the scooter but it's no good. However will they tell Elly? At first they try to cover up what they've done but eventually they have to confess. Thankfully Elly is not upset with them as she has another scooter and is just pleased her friends told the truth in the end.

title: Tea & Basketball
description: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys.

title: Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
description: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

title: Song of Sodor
description: When Nia suggests adding a song to spice up Sir Topham Hatt's new bench unveiling, he calls upon her to write a song for the ceremony, but Nia soon finds she may have bitten off more than she can sing.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Balloon
description: Bing, Sula and Flop find a balloon stuck in a tree and play the Stuckie Duckie game. Will Bing and Sula remember to stick together?

title: Upside Down
description: Pato gets stuck hanging upside down from the sky. Pocoyo and the friends try to help him down.

title: Prickly Pals/A Sting in the Tale/Tongue Twister
description: When Arlo plays too rough, Lucas forms a new friendship with a cactus./ Maizie accidentally stings Lucas's butt. This is a shock to them both, but Maizie takes it the hardest./ When Bodhi's tongue gets hurt, it's up to Dr. Lucas to help.

title: Pair O' Dice Lost
description: Daffy feels defeated whenever things aren't going his way.

title: Act Your Age
description: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

title: Pocoyo's Supermarket
description: Pocoyo and Pato have a supermarket. Elly calls them to order a bottle, which Pocoyo puts into a basket and delivers to her. Elly calls again to order a box and then a can. After several orders, Pocoyo and Pato are exhausted. Finally, Elly writes out a shopping list so that they can deliver everything at once with their cart.

title: Puff's Perfect Picnic
description: Because he has won the moss-ball game last year, Puff is in charge of organizing this Summer's Picnic. Only Puff isn't comfortable in that role. Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit offer to help and make sure all the Mushables will follow Puff's lead. Gradually, Puff gains confidence and ends up bossing everyone around. Now, all the Mushables are about to flee the Picnic!

title: Butterfly
description: Bing and his friends are playing at Amma's today when a beautiful butterfly comes inside. But what happens when Bing catches the butterfly in his hands while trying to save it?

title: The Big Sneeze
description: Elly has a cold and her huge trumpeting sneezes keep knocking Pocoyo's tower of bricks down. Pocoyo and Pato have to work out what to do.

title: Dino Fright
description: George P. Mandrake hires The Looney Builders to build a T. Rex fossil. It's Tweety's job to place the bones with his crane, but his fear of the big dino affects his ability to get the job done.

title: Pocoyo's Breakfast
description: It is breakfast time and Elly has made orange juice, milk and cereal for Pocoyo. But Pocoyo would rather see what his friends are having. So he sees that Fred is having seaweed, Baby Bird is having seeds, and his friends the Martians are having meteorites. His breakfast wasn't so bad after all!

title: The Mighty Boop and Fly Wonder/ Lucas and Findley get Antsy/ Mock Me Not
description: Lucas and Findley assume superhero personas, but Findley gets frustrated with being a sidekick. / The Mighty Boop and Fly Wonder find a lost baby ant. The duo is to the rescue! / Lucas playfully mimics Bodhi. But he may have offended her.

title: Now Museum, Now You Don't
description: Their very first trip to an art museum unleashes creative energy, turning the Baby Looney Tunes into enthused culture connoisseurs and budding artists. Baby Bugs recreates the museum experience back at Granny's house, finding abundant art history in everyday objects to the others' sheer delight.

title: Dizzy
description: Bing wants to do spinning on the spinny chair so Pando pushes him superfast. But what will happen when Bing starts to feel too dizzy and wants to stop?

title: Accidents Happen Boo Boo Song
description: Ella falls over, but Heidi the Horse teaches her to get right back up again!

title: Scary Noises
description: Pocoyo and Pato are out for an adventure in the Vamoosh but have to land on a strange planet when a part of the Vamoosh falls off. Whilst searching for the missing part, Pato gets scared because he hears a strange, scary noise. They both realize there is nothing to be scared of and the alien just wants to make friends.

title: Sliding/Spinning Webs
description: Lucas and Findley find an ice cube. When Lucas rides the ice cube in the sink and falls down the drain, a scared Findley rallies to save him./ Lucas questions his spider-hood when he can't spin a web properly.

title: The Big Rumble
description: A family of comically raucous rocks moves in near a Whiffle garden and drives them to distraction with their ground-pounding games. Funshine gets the rocks to leave. But when he learns their ground-pounding creates new soil, he must convince them to come back.

title: The Art of Friendship
description: When Chanterelle sees how good Lilit is at painting, she offers to help her dig into her talent. But Lilit's art lessons conflict with the fun project she has been working on with Mush-Mush and Chep. And when she sees that her friends are having a great time without her, Lilit is seriously annoyed which her paintings start showing.

title: Are We There Yet
description: During a long road trip, Floyd, obsessed with taking the Baby Looney Tunes to visit the distant, annual Acme Garlic Festival, endures countless variants of the universal kid question, are we there, yet? Despite Floyd's garlic agenda, fate has other plans.

title: Strike!
description: Pato is obsessed with bowling when he discovers that, no matter how hard he tries, he cannot hit any pins, whereas Elly and Pocoyo are doing it with no effort. Will Elly and Pocoyo manage to help him relax?

title: The Missing Mushlet
description: So Mushpie can take a break, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit offer to look after the Mushies, assuring her that everything will be fine. But a Mushie pops to become a Mushlet and escapes. Our friends find him in Muddler's clutches! Now, they must figure out a way to save the Mushlet and return the other Mushies to their cave before the return of Mushpie.

title: Did Not! Did Too!
description: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

title: Hearts
description: Bing and Sula choose their favourite things around the house and stickie them with hearts. What will happen when Sula gets to Bing's bedroom first?

title: Pocoyo's New Toys
description: Pato, Elly and Caterpillar are playing with their new toys: a hula hoop, a kite and a jump rope. Pocoyo is trying to play, but he doesn't know how. Good thing his friends lend him a hand and Pocoyo learns to play with all the toys.

title: Power Outage
description: The Care Bears come to the aid of a group of Whiffles whose worries are blanketing their garden with such bad vibes that plants won't grow. When the Care Bear Stare isn't powerful enough to help, Grumpy comes to the rescue with the invention of a robotic Care Bear Stare amplifier.

title: The Joke is on Thomas
description: When Thomas and Percy's plan to surprise Diesel goes awry, the two friends still manage to cheer up Diesel... just not in the way they expected!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Looking After Flop
description: Flop is sick and Bing explains that he wants to take care of him. So Bing tells Flop to sit on the sofa and gives him a pillow and a blanket, and Hoppity Voosh too! But making honey lemon is tricky hard.

title: Music is Everywhere
description: When music-lover Nia gets stranded before a big concert she's been waiting to see, Thomas brings the concert to her!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Nina Discovers the World
description: Pocoyo shows his knowledge by helping Nina learn the use of different objects. Nina is impressed, her friend seems to know everything! Or maybe not?

title: The Beepers: Funky Time
description: The Beepers play with tempo and learn that adapting to change can be…sweaty.

title: Mr Big Duck
description: Pato is enjoying playing at being very grown up and doesn't want to join in the games with his friends. Eventually though, Pato and the others realize that playing with friends is much more fun than hanging around being 'cool'.

title: The Legend of Big Butt/ Arlo Needs a Nap/ Everyone's a Critic
description: Lucas sets off to find the legendary monster, Big Butt, who roams the garden at night. / A sleepy Arlo avoids taking a nap, worried that he'll miss out on any fun. / Lucas struggles when his web-making skills are criticized.

title: Fool the Forest
description: It's Fool The Forest Day when Mushables pull pranks, and MM has an epic one planned. But they spill Chanterelle's painting dye and instead must replace it by finding a rare Sloof beetle and milking it for its dye in front of everyone. Wait a minute! You can't milk a beetle! They've been pranked!

title: Boingo/Findley's Bad Day/You Rang
description: Lucas, Findley and Bodhi become obsessed with a new toy called Boingo./ Findley is convinced House is out to get him./ Arlo is missing his mother, so Lucas gives him a bell to ring if he needs Lucas's help - bad idea.

title: Wheels
description: Our friends are out for a spin. Elly is riding her bike, Pocoyo is on his scooter and Pato is on his skateboard. Caterpillar also wants to ride with them but her friends' vehicles are too big for her. Thanks to her friends, in the end she manages to ride with them all.

title: Something to Remember
description: On the last day of Yong Bao's visit to Sodor, his friends dig up a giant keepsake to help him remember them.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Lightning Bugs Sylvester
description: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

title: Finders Keepers
description: When Dibble loses her beloved playball, the Care Bears are shocked to discover it has been taken by the Keeper, a mysterious figure who collects and stores away all items lost in the Silver Lining. To regain possession of the ball, the Bears and Dibble must help the Keeper recover a loss of his own.

title: Work Like a Charm
description: Chep becomes obsessed with learning all about Mushlore - all the funny little traditions and things that Mushables believe in. Morel is the expert in Mushlore so Chep becomes his apprentice. But the more Chep discovers about Mushlore the more he becomes a true believer to the point that it becomes quite dangerous!

title: These Little Piggies Went to Market
description: Their first trip to a big grocery store fascinates the Baby Looney Tunes. After warning the others to stick to Granny's shopping list, Baby Bugs succumbs to buying a favorite treat then feels guilty.

title: A Turtle Named Mrytle
description: A trip to the seashore brings the Baby Looney Tunes into contact with a just-hatched turtle that Melissa, apart from the rest because of her bossy attitude, names Myrtle. Melissa just loves little Myrtle and wants to keep her from walking into the ocean so she may take Myrtyle home for herself.

title: Mother's Day Madness
description: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

title: Ready, Steady, Go!
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly challenge each other to a race. Everything starts out well, but becomes more complicated as everyone begins to cheat so that they will arrive in first place. After various unexpected events everyone learns that winning isn't the most important and that it is more important to enjoy oneself.

title: Capture the Flag
description: When Percy loses Nia's parade flag before the big parade, Thomas helps them search for it before the event begins.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Big Scary Slide
description: There's lots of new exciting playground rides in Pocoyoland including one huge daring slide. Pocoyo is too scared to give it a go. Pocoyo bravely helps his friend and overcomes his fear.

title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

title: Surprise Machine
description: Bing and Sula are in Padget's Shop today when they discover the new surprise machine. But what will happen when Bing's surprise toy isn't the one he was hoping for?

title: The Magic of Spring
description: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

title: Let the Fun Shine
description: Expert skateboarder Funshine tries to duplicate the in-the-groove fun Dibble has when she rides her little cloud like a skateboard, but he discovers along the way that having fun isn't always about a better skateboard or riding a cloud, it can be about trying harder at something and finally succeeding.

title: Eggy Head
description: Bing and his friends are at Amma's creche today making Eggy Heads! Amma explains that Eggy Heads need 7 sleeps, water, light and patience to grow it's cress hair. But Bing has an idea to help his Eggy grow cress hair quicker...

title: Mountain
description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

title: Backstage Bugs
description: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

title: Color My World
description: Pocoyo finds a new toy - a remote control that changes the colors of the things around him. It's great fun until he changes the colors of his friends. We have to help him put things back to the way they were.

title: Wake up, Pocoyo! Wake up, Pocoyo!
description: The day begins and Pato gets out of bed full of energy, whereas Pocoyo cannot manage to wake up. Pato drags him out of bed and takes him to play, but Pocoyo is still sleepy. He gradually wakes up, but just when he really starts having fun, it is time to go to bed again.

title: Hair Cut-Ups
description: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut.

title: Getting Truffy with It
description: Truff is happy. He has found a necklace that makes him even Truffier! Except he had no idea the necklace belongs to Starmush. And the Mushelder promised there will be consequences for whoever took it. Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit now have to save Truff from being consequenced.

title: Rainy Boots
description: It's a wet, drippy day and Bing has his rainy boots on to help Flop take the trash out. While splish splashing outside, what will happen when Bing does a BIG SPLASH and finds his rainy boots have holes in them?

title: Pato's Egg
description: Pato finds an egg and immediately falls in love with it: he wants to take care of the little baby inside the egg. When the egg hatches he gets the shock of his life: it's not a cute little duckling at all, but a very odd looking spider. His friends are terrified of the little creature and won't play with Pato if he brings it along. Pato rather craftily and meanly makes the little spider go away and do things on its own, so Pato can play with Pocoyo and Elly. Finally the little spider makes their hearts melt when he shows them that there's nothing to be scared of and he just wants to be their friend.

title: Alpha Bodies
description: Cartoonito presents Alpha Bodies! It's time to use our bodies to make every letter of the alphabet, from A to Z, but one over-eager letter keeps getting ahead of itself.

title: Bats
description: Can you see in the dark? Blippi can't either! But on this adventure Blippi and FETCH fly around in the dark with Matt the Bat who shows them how he uses echolocation to see and hear in the dark! Who needs eyes when you can use echo-echo-echoes?

title: Blippi Learns Rainbow Colors
description: Have you ever wondered how a rainbow gets its colors? Join Blippi and his sidekick TABBS on their first adventure as they discover the science behind rainbows!

title: More
description: It's bath time! Bing's excited to do the bubbles, but how much bubble goo does Bing need?

title: The Guardian of the Forest
description: Mush-Mush wants to impress the Mushlets by showing off his sensing gift. But his sense-foot doesn't work like it should. This is a disaster! And when Mushpot explains that some Mushables have to wait until they become Mushups to see their gifts fully developed, Mush-Mush is frustrated. He wants to master his gift now! Mush-Mush discovers that the solution he's looking for might be in The Dark Dark Forest. Mush-Mush decides to take his friends Chep and Lilit on a little trip.

title: Tree
description: Bing and Pando are being diggers, planting trees in the sandpit. What will happen when Pando ruins Bing's digging?

title: Cell Phone
description: Bing and Hoppity want to play with Talking Lettuce on Flops cell phone. Bing remembers to put the cell phone down when he wants to voosh with Hoppity. But what happens when Bing vooshes a little too close to Flop's cell phone?

title: Pocoyo's Camera
description: Pocoyo finds a camera and goes looking for his friends to take pictures of them. He catches his friends by surprise and they don't like the pictures he has taken of them. In the end, they all take much better pictures of each other and have fun together.

title: Mushlers to the Rescue
description: Having rescued a Mushlet, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit become heroes in Mushton, and they're loving it! So Mushlers create a rescue team but alas, no one needs saving! How can you be a hero when there is nothing to be heroic about? Then when some Mushlets become adrift on the river, Team Mush-Mush, with Morel's help, have to save the day again.

title: A Day With Starmush
description: Mush-Mush wants to be just like Starmush when he grows up, because he's convinced that Starmush is the most awesome Mushable there is and that his daily life must be extraordinary. So, Mush-Mush trails Starmush, which soon annoys the Mushelder. To get rid of Mush-Mush, Starmush decides to live up to the Mushler's fantasies…

title: Snow Cap
description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

title: The Key to it All
description: Pocoyo finds a key which leads him on an exciting and magical adventure of exploration and discovery.

title: The Disappearing Mushler
description: Mush-Mush can't wait to show his tricks of forest illusion to everyone. But Amanita keeps ruining Mush-Mush's performance by figuring out all his tricks. Grrr! When Mush-Mush decides to do his famous 'Disappearing Mushable' trick on Truff, Truff really disappears! And now, Amanita and Mush-Mush must join forces to find their disappearing friend.

title: Invisible Pocoyo
