description: Pocoyo finds a fantastic new toy: a machine that makes things invisible! He wants to show his friends his exciting discovery but they are too busy doing their own thing. Pocoyo is miffed but then realizes that he can have some fun with them, without them knowing about it. He makes himself invisible and starts to undertake various sneaky antics which utterly dumbfound his pals. Things get out of hand when Pato blames Elly and Elly blames Pato - even though we all know it's really Pocoyo's fault. Finally the truth is revealed when Baby Bird presses the button on the machine and Pocoyo is de-invisible-ised! In the end, they all play at being invisible together.

title: Log Cabin Fever
description: Granny takes the Baby Looney Tunes back to a simpler lifestyle during a rustic weekend spent in an 1800's log cabin, where they learn to enjoy life minus all modern conveniences. Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy get in trouble for smuggling their palm-sized computer game along, and they face Granny's consequences.

title: Elly's Tea Party
description: Elly invites her chums to a tea party but they don't want to come because they know how bossy Elly is at her tea parties. The tea parties are no fun because Elly is always barking out rules and orders. But when Pocoyo and Pato smell Elly's gorgeous biscuits, they realize what they're missing out on and they change their minds. They really want to go to her tea party now. Before they can dig into the biscuits though, Elly bosses them around. Pocoyo and Pato are exasperated and leave Elly to it. Elly realizes that her friends are sad, and a tea party isn't really a tea party unless you've got friends there with you. So Elly stops being bossy, and they all have a fun party eating the treats together.

title: Nature Explorer
description: Bing and his friends are Nature Explorers today! But what will happen when Bing is nature exploring by a big, prickly bush?

title: Double Trouble
description: Pocoyo wants to play ball but Pato is stubborn: he wants to play on the see-saw. Elly turns up so Pocoyo goes to play catch with her. Pato's left on his own. And the see-saw is no fun on your own. But he has an idea. He gets a machine and makes a copy of himself, a clone. The clone likes playing for a while but when they both want to play with the same toy car, they fall out. So Pato makes another Pato. Every time he makes a new Pato, something goes wrong, because the Patos all want the same thing and are as stubborn as each other. Finally, one of the clone Patos clones itself and soon there are crowds of Patos rampaging all around the place. Pocoyo and Elly to the rescue! They turn off the machine and all the copy Patos disappear. Phewy. To end, Pato plays ball.

title: Elly's Playhouse
description: Elly has a playhouse to play in. Her house has a door, a roof and a window. But when Pocoyo and Pato play with her, the playhouse comes down. With Elly's help, they manage to put it back together, placing everything back in its place.

title: Cat-Taz-Trophy
description: Sylvester and Taz team up to win a toy racecar derby.

title: If It's Broke, Fix It
description: Dibble helps Grumpy work on his latest invention, a device to stop Bluster's bad vibe plow. Dibble's endless high spirits and sense of fun wear on Grumpy, until he finally says she can't work with him anymore. It's only later that Grumpy understands he needs Dibble's free-spirit inventiveness and creative energy.

title: On the Trail of the Cloud Bouncer
description: When spores from a strange plant take over control of the Cloudseeker, Cheer and the team must risk losing the vehicle - their home away from home and their only way back to Care-A-Lot - in order to save the Whiffles' newly-planted valley.

title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

title: Pocoyo and the Haunted House
description: In this spooky episode, Pocoyo and Pato go trick and treat and visit a haunted house with all sorts of frights and jokes, where nothing is what it looks like.

title: Tiny Fun Park
description: The buses to the theme park are absolutely packed, so Nina shrinks all her friends. Now that they're tiny, any object can be a theme park ride! Sometimes things don't go as planned...they go so much better!

title: Lost and Found
description: When Thomas helps Nia make a delivery to the beach in Norramby, he insists he knows a shortcut and leads the way! But it turns out his memory isn't as good as he… remembered.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Lightning Bark
description: Fung and Miff have come across a rare piece of bark struck by lightning. Chep desperately wants to add it to his collection, but Fung and Miff have no intention to give it to him. Now remembering every time Chep has been nice to them, Fung and Miff end up doing something they never thought possible…

title: Gravity
description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

title: First Car
description: No kind of travel is too difficult for the BlippiMobile, not even TIME travel! Blippi and FETCH head back in time to see what the first cars were like, and who better to show him than Blippi's great-grandpa Blippi! It's a harrowing ride, but along the way Blippi finds the answers he's looking for.

title: Up & Down
description: Pocoyo is showing Baby Bird the difference between up and down. To do this, they are playing on the teeter-totter, but Baby Bird is still not quite sure what is up and what is down. They go up to the top of the slide and slide down. But he still has doubts. Finally, they take a ride in the Vamoosh. Baby Bird finally gets it!

title: Elly's Bath
description: Pocoyo is looking for Elly to play ball, but Elly is taking a bath. While Pocoyo waits, Elly plays with the bubbles and her rubber ducky in the tub. Elly finally gets out of the bathtub, but Pocoyo doesn't feel like playing ball anymore. He wants to play in the bathtub too!

title: Ducks
description: Blippi gets up close and personal with Declan the Duck in his quest to find how ducks float! Under the water, above the water, through feather tunnels and tooting air bubbles, Blippi and Declan work together to discover the answer.

title: Bandages
description: Bing and Coco are nurses today after Coco gets a paper cut on her finger and needs a bandage. But Bing would like a bandage too, and makes one from sticky tape. But what will happen when he tries to take it off and it hurts?

title: The Tennis Racket
description: The kids are playing tennis, but Elly gets upset with Pato and Pocoyo because they won't follow the rules. Will they manage to enjoy their game?

title: Pocoyo's Scary Halloween
description: It's Halloween and Pocoyo and friends are working on their costumes. Pocoyo is excited because he has prepared a surprise - he has hired Chihuahua Brothers to scare his friends! Who will scare who?

title: My Pato
description: Pato and Elly are arguing over their blocks when Caterpillar and Baby Bird walk past with presents for Pato. Oh no! Pocoyo and Elly have forgotten Pato's birthday. Elly is quick to whisk Pato off to a birthday picnic, determined to prove how much she cares. Not to be outdone, quick-thinking Pocoyo appears at the picnic with a present but Elly retaliates and 'accidentally' breaks it. Pocoyo and Elly fight so hard over Pato that he's almost broken in two. Fed up with all the fight Pato packs his things and is about to leave. When Pocoyo and Elly realize that their fighting has driven Pato away, they quickly make up and turn their efforts into making a special birthday party for Pato.

title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

title: Bouncing Back
description: Mush-Mush is very proud he invented a new game called Fruity Bounce, where he and his friends bounce as high as possible on the bouncier fruits they can find. Little did he know, the Mushups were fruit-bouncing way before he, Chep and Lilit did. So, Mush-Mush decides that if he can't be the inventor of the game, he'll at least be the best at it. Mushlers vs Mushups, game on!

title: Race for the Sodor Cup
description: Super-fast Kana is convinced that her speed is all she needs to win the world renowned Race for the Sodor Cup. However, when she ends up paired with Thomas for the games, she discovers that it takes much more than speed to really be a champion.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Dog's Life
description: Pocoyo pretends to be an elephant, a duck and a dog - but when Loula needs his help, Pocoyo sees that sometimes it's best just to be himself.

title: Splash Zone
description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

title: Dark
description: It's time for bed, but where's Hoppity? Bing thinks he's left him outside, and now, it's all dark... With the help of Flop and his carroty torch, can Bing find Hoppity in time for bed?

title: Duck! Monster! Duck!
description: Daffy reads the babies a scary story, only to end up frightening himself.

title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

title: Leader of the Pack
description: Daffy starts a secret password club for everyone except Bugs.

title: Hush
description: Pocoyo and his gang want to make friends with a butterfly but every time they say hello, it flies away. With Sleepy Bird's help, they realize how to get close to the butterfly.

title: Pocoyo, Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo discovers a fabulous new playmate - his echoooo-ooo-ooo-ooo!

title: Percy Disappears
description: On their way to a celebration for Thomas' 10,000th delivery, Percy tries to help Thomas with his big speech, but Thomas fails to listen. While distracted, Thomas doesn't notice when Percy falls off the track and gets lost. Percy tries unsuccessfully to find his way to familiar terrain. Thomas realizes he wasn't listening to Percy after all! He abandons his delivery ceremony to find Percy! Thomas uses what he knows about his best friend to track him down, proving how well he knows his loc-amigo.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Sneaky Shoes
description: Pato, Pocoyo and Elly are having fun doing running and jumping competitions: except Pato is taking it very seriously. So when he loses he's mighty miffed. He is a very bad loser. He goes off in a huff and finds some swanky sneakers. He tries them on and discovers that these are no ordinary sneakers: they have a life of their own, they have super powers. Once he's mastered them he challenges Pocoyo and Elly to a re-match. Of course now he wins the running and jumping contests hands down. But Elly feels that something's up and doesn't want to compete anymore. When Pato tries to take the shoes off he realizes they won't undo. He's stuck and the shoes are going crazy. Luckily Caterpillar and Baby Bird save the day by getting the shoes off. And Pato has learnt that cheating just isn't a good way to win.

title: Pato, The Postman
description: Pocoyo writes a letter to Elly but needs a postman to deliver it. Luckily Pato is ready to deliver Pocoyo's mail, as well as the post of everyone else. The situation gets out of control as poor Pato is not able to keep up with the post. When his friends realize this, they send him on his last delivery that will land him at a surprise party they can enjoy together.

title: A Song for Wimble/ I Want My Baby Acorn Back/ The Giggles
description: Findley becomes nervous when he's put in charge of taking care of House while Lucas is away./ Lucas and Findley are a little unnerved by the thunder and lightning happening outside their window. But Arlo is there to help them through it!/ Dr. Lucas is in the house when Findley says he has a cold. But is Findley being truthful?

title: Planets
description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

title: Thomas' Day Off
description: When all the trains but Thomas get deliveries, he's left to spend the day alone. With the help of an old boxcar and a battered beachball... an adventure unfolds.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Fast Friends
description: While Kana and Thomas deliver aquarium materials for the Vicarstown Fish Day, it's up to steady Percy and Nia to deliver the fish themselves. However, Nia gets a wobbly wheel, inciting Percy to ask Kana for a switch so she can help Nia and speed up the delivery. Once Nia is fixed, she's raring to go, but Kana unexpectedly wants to slow things down to keep the fish safe. Could this quarrel spell doom for the delivery or allow these engines to learn something they never realized about each other?
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Pocoyo's Puppet Theater
description: Pocoyo finds a box full of puppets. Elly helps him build a puppet theater to play with. Now they have puppets and a puppet theater with its curtain, but they are still missing one important thing: the audience!

title: Chasing Rainbows
description: Thomas and Kana journey across Sodor to find the prize at the end of a rainbow.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Salad Salsa
description: Mei, Ella, animals cook a delicious salad using local vegetables

title: A Yoorg Awakening
description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

title: A Wide Delivery
description: When the trains must deliver in pairs, Thomas is disappointed to be paired with Diesel instead of his BFF Percy.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Yip Yip, Book Book!/Stick to It!
description: It's the Pretty Big All City Read and Izzy and Barb are ready, that is, until all the books go missing!/Pretty Big City finds itself in a sticky situation when the factory starts spewing super sticky slime everywhere!

title: Going to the Beach
description: Pocoyo and Pato receive a postcard from Elly, who is on vacation at the beach. Not to be outdone, they set up their own beach. All ready with their sunglasses, a bucket and shovel, they build a fantastic sandcastle. Now they just have to wait for Elly to get back so they can all play at their beach together.

title: Mine!
description: Daffy learns a lesson in doing the right thing when he finds a purse filled with money.

title: Pato's Paintings
description: Everyone's preparing for a painting exhibition. Everyone except Pato who says he's not bothered about painting. When the show opens, Pato unexpectedly exhibits his paintings: they are amazing masterpieces (Actually they are real masterpieces. He didn't paint them!). Everyone is very impressed and asks him to paint another. But he can't, because in fact he cheated: he didn't paint these pictures at all. Pocoyo and the audience encourage Pato to have a go at painting. He paints a beautiful flower and feels very pleased with himself. His painting takes its place in the exhibition.

title: The Tiger Train
description: When Yong Bao visits Sodor, a jealous Thomas sets out to prove he's the braver train and challenges Yong Bao to a series of bravery challenges, only to have his plan backfire.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Ahoy, Pocoyo!
description: Our friends have become pirates. With the help of a map and a telescope, they find the treasure chest on the island. They manage to get past the watchful eye of the evil monster that is guarding it to discover the fantastic treasure hidden inside the chest.

title: The Last Laugh
description: Disappointed when his friends don't laugh at his jokes, Funshine encounters the Laffinpuff, a magical comedian who grants Funshine's wish to make everyone think he's funny. But Funshine realizes it's no fun being funny when people laugh at everything he says, whether he means it to be funny or not. To get the wish rescinded, he must face the Laffinpuff in a grueling ordeal of slapstick humor.

title: Where Oh Where Has Our Funshine Gone?
description: When Funshine uses the Care Bears' work time to develop his latest comic book character, his creative playtime jeopardizes the success of the team's mission to a strange part of the Silver Lining.

title: Ashima's Amazing Arrival
description: When Ashima is set to arrive on Sodor, Thomas and friends attempt to go the extra mile in order to make the island seem fantastic! Thomas plans an extraordinary welcome that includes a tiger, painted dock, and big dance number. But when the spectacular plan gets ruined at every turn, the friends imperfect welcome still makes Ashima's arrival extra special.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Juggling Balls
description: Pocoyo is very impressed with Elly and Octopus' trick of juggling. He wants to play too. Octopus makes Pocoyo practice lots of different activities but Pocoyo can't see the point because they aren't related to juggling… or so he thinks. In the end Pocoyo becomes the star of the show!

title: Hello Around the World
description: Cartoonito presents Hello Around the World! All across the globe, friends greet each other in lots of different languages. Watch along and discover some of the many ways to say "Hello," around the world and beyond!

title: Prank Day
description: It's Prank Day and Pocoyo is having fun at his friends' expense. But then they all decide to get back at him. How will he take it?

title: The Biggest Adventure Club
description: When Thomas finds a treasure map he creates "The Big Adventure Club," to seek the treasure, but when Sandy wants to join, Thomas says she's too little, so Sandy forms her own club.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Shadow
description: Bing is playing shadow tag with Flop, but what will happen when the clouds come?

title: Pocoyo's Little Friend
description: Pocoyo finds a new little friend - a very hungry caterpillar. He watches with amazement as his new friend transforms.

title: The Ultimate Bad Seed
description: Malcom becomes the new boss of Blusterland when he tricks Bluster into letting him transfer his inner-badness into a Bad Seed, leaving Bluster a polite shell of his former self. To neutralize the dangerous Seed before Malcom can use it to turn the Silver Lining into a giant Blusterland, the Care Bears must transfer its bad energy back into the only thing that can hold it, Bluster himself!

title: Sandy's Sandy Shipment
description: When Sandy learns about a massive shipment of sand that needs to be delivered, she is determined to help despite her size.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Picture This
description: Pocoyo imagines that fish live in different places and draws funny pictures for his friends.

title: Moo-ving Day!/Follow That Breeze
description: Zee's growth ray turns Moobert giant, but when a storm rolls in, the Mechas need to build a shelter big enough to fit her./After Ranger Nat's kite blows away in the wind, the Mechas and Timmy learn to build their own kite to find it.

title: Some Luck
description: While the Bears are transporting a Whiffle Wizard to a distant meadow, Good Luck seems to have a run of bad luck. His belief in his own bad fortune causes him to lose confidence, causing ever more "bad luck." It's only when he understands that we make our own luck that his "luck" changes.

title: Boo!
description: Pocoyo has a new game which he enjoys playing on his friends: BOO! Only some of his friends find Pocoyo's game annoying or frightening. But this only encourages Pocoyo more. He boos poor Pato til he ends up a nervous wreck. Elly sees how scared Pato has become and decides to give Pocoyo a taste of his own medicine. Elly makes Pocoyo jump. At first Pocoyo doesn't like it but ultimately Pato and Pocoyo both realize it can be fun to BOO! and to be BOOED!

title: The Beepers: Spotlight
description: When a spotlight gives everyone a chance to solo, a shy Beeper discovers the courage to shine.

title: Bye Bye
description: Bing loves playing with his new orange balloon, but what will happen when he bounces on it too much?

title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

title: Dance Off Part Two
description: Elly and Nina are dancing in synch. Pocoyo and Pato enter the scene and challenge them to a dance off. Who will be the best dance duo? Even Roberto joins the party. Can't stop! Won't stop!

title: Poczilla
description: Pocoyo and Pato are playing at being terrifying giant monsters, like the sort of monsters they've seen in their comics. They find a toy city and enjoy being like Godzilla and King Kong. They don't notice that the little toys who live in the city are scared and that they're all running away in terror as Pocoyo and Pato destroy their toy city. The audience tells Pocoyo and Pato to stop. Once Pocoyo and Pato realize what's been going on they repair the damage and make a wonderful funfair for the little toys.

title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

title: Something for Sula
description: Bing is making a picture for Sula with all of her favourite things on. Will Bing make Sula the perfect picture?

title: Sleep Guard
description: Sleepy Bird is getting ready for a peaceful nap, but Pocoyo is banging away on his drum. Pocoyo promises to be quiet and help Sleepy Bird get some much needed sleep, but that's harder than it seems.

title: Frog
description: Bing and Sula find a frog in the garden, but will Froggy like her new bucket house?

title: Bath Song
description: Ella gets covered in mud so she goes into Mei's farmhouse to have a bath.

title: Birds Nest
description: A storm has destroyed Jodie the Blue Jays bird nest! Good thing Blippi and FETCH are there to help. While FETCH is on egg-sitting duty, Jodie and Blippi go on a heist mission to acquire the materials needed to rebuild. It's never an impossible mission when friends work together!

title: Overprotective Roberto
description: When Nina gets a small scrape while playing, Roberto becomes obsessed with protecting her. But he goes over the top and poor Nina cannot even play or have fun with Pocoyo and friends! What can they do?

title: O'Little Tree
description: Mei shows Ella and Rishi the magic of Christmas - by growing an adorable Christmas tree in the middle of the farm.

title: Hiccup
description: Pato gets the hiccups. Together Pocoyo, Elly and Loula help him to get rid of them by giving him a surprise.

title: Dare For More
description: Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit are playing dares and having a lot fun. All the Mushables are happy for them except Fung and Miff who keep mocking them. When Mush-Mush reply they should play together to see how fun it is, Fung and Miff accept. Mush-Mush surprisingly gets along with Fung and Miff until one dare too many.

title: Duck's Reflucks
description: Baby Daffy has Baby Bugs right where he wants him, as the subject of his digital photography and at the mercy of his endless, egocentric creative whims.

title: After the Klatternack
description: The Care Bears try to capture the Klatternack, a comical creature whose non-stop nonsense is annoying the local Whiffles. The Bears are joined by the ultra-serious Tracker, who has long been after the Klatternack himself. But despite their combined efforts, the wily creature continues to elude them - until Share realizes there is more going on than meets the eye.

title: Fireworks
description: Bing is excited to watch the Fireworks outside, but will they be too noisy loud?

title: Roller Coasting
description: Thomas wants to show Percy what it's like to ride a roller coaster, so Thomas turns the tracks of Sodor into a thrill ride.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: For Whom the Toll Calls
description: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill.

title: The Adventurers
description: Because Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit are always up to new adventures, Bolly has dubbed them The Adventurers. Flattered, our friends invite Bolly to choose his challenge to become an Adventurer too. Bolly will have to be the first Mushable to set foot somewhere. Mushton being crowded, Mush-Mush suggests they find an island, somewhere on the giant lake.

title: Nina the Dog Trainer
description: Nina agrees to train Loula for a day, but she is so convinced that it's a simple task that she ignores Pocoyo's advice, landing her in trouble. What will happen?

title: Sparkle Magic
description: Sula is the fairy queen and shows Bing her special sparkle magic... will Bing find his own?

title: Playing Dress Up
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Pato are playing dress up. Elly has put on some polka-dotted shoes, Pato is wearing a red hat and bow tie, and Pocoyo is wearing some yellow trousers. Caterpillar wants to play with them, but finds nothing in her size. With a little imagination, Caterpillar gets her own costume.

title: Eggsellent Adventure
description: Thomas and Percy have a difficult delivery - getting eggs and other cake ingredients safely to Vicarstown for their bake-off.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Pocoyo's Puppet Show
description: Pocoyo finds a puppet theatre and some puppets. Brilliant! Time for him to be a puppeteer. He puts on a show for Caterpillar and Baby Bird. They love it, especially when the puppets do funny things like fall over. They bring Pato and Elly along to watch the show too. When Pocoyo makes fun of Pato and Elly with the puppets, Pato and Elly are nonplussed. They don't think it's so great to laugh at people. Pocoyo realizes that his show has upset his friends. He says sorry and explains he didn't mean it. Everyone makes friends again!

title: Eyes on the Surprise
description: Every time Mush-Mush has tried to surprise his friend with a gift, Chep has always found out what it was. But Chep promises that this time he won't. And Lilit, who is too honest to keep a secret, promises she won't let Chep know what the surprise is. Both of them find this so hard! But Mush-Mush is one step ahead of them…

title: Neon Beach Party
description: Bluster and his Bad Crowd arrive at a lakeside beach for his summer vacation, unaware that the Care Bears are having their vacation on the opposite shore. Trapped inside Bluster's climate-control dome and forced to spend their vacations together, the Bears must find a way to make friends with their ill-tempered neighbors.

title: Squirrels
description: Blippi and FETCH are going on a treasure hunt! For Squirrel treasure that is. Their new friend Sparky the Squirrel has her nuts buried all over the park and Blippi tries to remember where she buried them. Sparky remembers them all though and Blippi learns why squirrels bury their nuts.

title: The Reflection
description: It's Halloween and everyone is dressing up. Pocoyo, as a wizard, is practicing scaring in front of the mirror and inadvertently makes his Reflection come alive! His Reflection looks just like him but is far more mischievous. The Reflection soon discovers that he can get sweets by scaring people and starts going after all of Pocoyo's friends. They think it's the real Pocoyo, so the Reflection is causing a lot of trouble for poor Pocoyo. Will he be able to clear up the confusion?

title: Morel in the Dark
description: When Mush-Mush discovers that Morel is afraid of the dark, he suggests that Chep, Lilit and he take the Mushlets to their first overnight forest camp. Morel is relieved. But when Mush-Mush and his friends later come back, panicked, and reveal that the Mushlets have disappeared, Morel has no choice but to face his fear and join our friends on their rescue mission in the dark!

title: Dance Off!
description: Pocoyo and Pato stumble upon a disco and Elly is the DJ. Pato gets grooving to a track and Elly thinks he's fantastic. But Pocoyo's not impressed. He has a go and shows his dance. It's wonderful, but then Pato thinks he can do even better. And so it goes on - an impromptu, ever-so-funky dance off! Things get out of hand when Pocoyo is raving and Pato is body-popping so Elly changes the record. She takes to the dance floor and shows the rivals - in an uncannily Britney-esque way - that instead of competing, they can all have fun dancing together! It's much more fun.

title: Takers Keepers
description: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want.

title: Umbrella, Umbrella
description: Pocoyo finds an umbrella. He and his friends have great fun playing with the umbrella and trying to work out what it's for. When it starts to rain, Pocoyo - with the help of the children watching - realizes a perfect use for it!

title: Dragon Island
description: Will Pocoyo and his friends manage to find the Dragon hiding in Las Palmas de Gran Canaria?

title: Save the Fun Tree
description: Mush-Mush and friends' favorite play tree, the Fun Tree, is rotten and doomed. But Mush-Mush refuses to give up on it. In a last ditch effort to save the tree, our friends adventure off to try and track down the legendary Starmush, hoping his mysterious healing powers can save it.

title: Tennis for Everyone
description: Our friends are preparing for a tennis game. Pato is a grand champion and it seems that no one can challenge his superiority on the court. When Valentina offers to play him, everyone laughs because she is so small. At the end of the episode Valentina shows that even someone as small as her can be a great champion.

title: Party Pooper
description: Pocoyo is having a party and invites all his friends. But instead of letting his friends have fun, Pocoyo keeps bossing them around. Pato, Elly and Fred soon get fed up and leave the party to play their own way. Left to play on his own, Pocoyo realizes that a party with no guests is no fun at all. Pocoyo invites his friends back to the party and everyone has fun playing together in their own unique and individual ways.

title: Band Together
description: The babies learn about music and improvise their own orchestra.

title: No Power, No Problem!
description: When the power goes out all over Sodor, Thomas and Friends must use brain-power to navigate the island in creative new ways.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
description: Thomas and the other Engines get to deliver some newly discovered dinosaur bones, but they must deliver them in the correct order for assembly, which isn't as easy as it sounds...
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: In Bugs We Trust
description: Bugs uses the babies' money to buy different toys than he promised.

title: Lunch
description: Bing and Sula are chefs today and helping Amma and Flop make lunch. It's Sula's favourite - Easy Peasy Pasta! But, what happens when lunch is served and Bing sees all the ingredients mixed up together?

title: New on the Planet
description: Pocoyo is scared when a stranger appears in Pocoyoland, but he soon comes to realize that he needn't be scared of this little alien and they become friends.

title: Return of the Gnomes
description: When Gus and Garth's greedy uncle makes his nephews forget the caring, sharing, and generosity they learned from the Care Bears and convinces them to return to their old selfish ways, the Bears must help them remember their caring hearts.

title: Smash House
description: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that's smash-proof.

title: A Mystery Most Puzzling
description: Pocoyo has to follow the clues in a series of photographs to work out who's got the camera.

title: Calliope Crack-Up
description: When the engines are delivering attractions to the annual Harwick Beach Carnival, a series of mistakes causes the precious Calliope to break. Luckily, the engines come up with a creative solution.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Once Upon a Rainbow
description: When Grumpy mysteriously loses his blue color in a far-off area of the Silver Lining, the Bears track down the cause: a creature called the Painter has lost the key to the magical paintbox that creates all the color in the area. Grumpy must recover the key to restore his blueness.

title: Where's Pocoyo?
description: Pocoyo plays hide and seek with us. Can you find him?

title: Honey
description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

title: Pocoyo's Car
description: Unwilling to accept that he has grown too big for his old toy car, Pocoyo will get into some crazy trouble and even argue with his friends! How will it end?

title: Percy's Lucky Bell
description: When Thomas borrows Percy's lucky bell for a dangerous delivery, Thomas isn't careful and loses the bell.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Splash Song
description: Ella is drawing a bus when she lets her imagination runs wild!

title: Blocks
description: Bing is building a tower with his blocks but what will happen when both he and Coco want the last red block?

title: Knack
description: Bing, Sula and Pando are in the garden trying to find out what everyone's knack is. Will Bing find his own knack?

title: The Dino Box
description: Pato tries out Pocoyo's latest invention, the Dino box, and is transformed into a dinosaur! Pocoyo loves his new pet, but looking after a dinosaur is very difficult... especially when Elly is also transformed. What will happen?

title: Runaway Hat
description: It's a windy day and Pato's hat gets blown away. Pato doesn't like the way he looks without his hat and he's afraid his friends will laugh at him so he hides and won't play. Finally they catch up with him and he tries on a selection of replacement hats, none of which quite fit the bill. When Elly and Pocoyo realize what's wrong they don't understand Pato's reaction. They like the way he looks. Pato comes to see that his friends love him for who he is, not what he looks like and the friends all play happily together.

title: The Grumpy Effect
description: Bluster traps Grumpy in a frustration-inducing labyrinth in an attempt to capture his grumpiness and turn it into the ultimate Bad Seed, which when planted will create new areas of Blusterland. The scheme backfires when Bluster refuses to listen to the warnings of his underlings, and Grumpy's inner kindness turns the Bad Seed into a force for good.

title: What's In the Box?
description: Pocoyo's new box takes on a life of its own when Loula accidentally crawls underneath it. Eventually with the help of his friends, Pocoyo works out what's - or WHO'S - in the box.

title: Mushpot's Treasure
description: When Mushpot wishes he could roll back the seasons and relive being a Mushler, our friends get him to hang out doing cool Mushler stuff. But this just shows that Mushpot is no longer able to do all those things. Sigh! However, when our friends find a map that points to a treasure he buried when he was a Mushler, Mushpot realises it's just the Mushler experience he needed.

title: Hide and Sneak
description: Dibble is chosen as "It" in a Whiffle game of Hide-and-Seek. The game turns serious when Bluster traps the Bears inside the Cloudseeker. Dibble and Cheer must find the Whiffles and free her friends.

title: Slippery Pato
description: Pato puts on so much oil that he becomes very slippery and can't even play with his friends. At the beginning he loves it, but he soon discovers that too much oil has its drawbacks. Will Pato be able to regain his normal plumage?

title: Mushroomates
description: When ants invade Fung and Miff's tree, our Mushlers offer for them to move in but the two quickly turn out to be unbearable roommates. So when Fung and Miff break their trampoline, our friends decide it's time for them to go back to their homes. But first they need to get rid of the ants.

title: The Snake Dance
description: When Mush-Mush and Chep lose Lilit's flying disc down a snake tunnel, he is confident he can get it back. All animals love Chep and no one knows more about snakes than he does. But this snake is not to be messed with! When they finally sneak into the snake tunnel, they learn why the snake has been acting so strangely…

title: Blast Off Bugs
description: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit.

title: Boo
description: Coco shows Bing how to do really big boos, but what will happen when Bing wants to practice on Charlie?

title: I'm Taking You In/Something Up There/Home Sweet Home
description: When Arlo's mom is out, Lucas looks after him. How hard can it be?/ After hearing a screech from the fireplace, Lucas journeys up to find what is causing the noise./ Lucas and friends find a Gingerbread House and can't resist eating it.

title: Travel with Pato
description: Pato is about to go away on a trip on an airplane but realizes that he has forgotten his suitcase. He calls Pocoyo and Elly and begs them to bring it as fast as possible to the airport. They take the bus and the train to try and get to the airport before Pato's flight takes off.

title: A Frog of a Problem
description: MM's favorite frog has had its home taken over by a lizard. Mushpot says not to interfere, nature must run its course. But Lilit feels so sorry for the frog she takes it back to Mushton where it causes havoc. Now our friends must lure the frog back to its home where it deals with the lizard itself.

title: House of Colors
description: Elly has a new house and wants to paint it pink. She asks Pocoyo and Pato for help, but they want to paint it a different color. Teamwork involves compromise! They'll find a way to paint it a color they all like, that's for sure.

title: Sneeze
description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

title: The Light in the Forest
description: Cheer bonds with a migrating firefly-like creature, called a Sparklewing, who stows aboard the Cloudseeker. The two become good friends, but there's a problem: Sparklewings must finish their migration to bring life-giving nutrients to the fields of the Silver Lining. Cheer's difficult and emotional parting with her new friend is only possible once they both accept that it's for a greater good.

title: Dragon Breath
description: Bing and Pando are blowing steamy dragon breath outside when they find an icicle that makes Bing's hands icy cold! So they go inside for some hot chocolate. What happens when Bing doesn't wait for the hot chocolate to cool down?

title: Flash and Boom/ House Sitting/ Findley is Sick
description: Lucas and Findley are unnerved by the thunder and lightning. But Arlo helps them through it! / Findley is nervous about taking care of House while Lucas is away. / Findley fibs about being sick to avoid chores. Dr. Lucas isn't happy.

title: Monster Mystery
description: Pocoyo makes a monster mask out of an old box. When he fails to scare Elly and Pato, he kicks the box out of the way in frustration. The box lands on Sleepy Bird who can't get out of it. She flies close to Pocoyo to ask for help but he and his friends are terrified. A chase ensues. Finally Baby Bird works it out. It was Sleepy Bird all along. The friends all have a monster mash party together at the end.

title: Pocoyo's Balloon
description: Pocoyo is taking a walk with his beloved balloon when he is momentarily distracted by Loula and accidentally lets go of the balloon. He is flabbergasted as it drifts away up into the sky, and irreconcilably down in the dumps. Until we help him to realize that some things are more lasting than balloons: friends!

title: A Bully for Bugs
description: With Floyd's adult assistance, Baby Bugs and the Baby Looney Tunes learn an effective way to deal with a bully.

title: Pouting Match
description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

title: Who's' calling Me Now?
description: Pocoyo finds a box of unusual whistles. To his delight he discovers that each whistle makes a different noise and summons a different one of his chums. Fun until the tables are turned on Pocoyo and there's a whistle that summons him too. Everyone realizes how silly they're being.

title: Train
description: Bing's train can do lots of great things in the park's playground, but as Bing and Pando climb higher, what else will the train do?

title: The Balloon
description: Pocoyo and Pato lose Nina's balloon and must try to recover it, but Angry Alien has found it and has no intention of returning it. Will they be able to get it back?

title: The Brave Little Tweety
description: Tweety takes a role in a play too seriously and begins to believe he's a real superhero.

title: Skiff Sails Sodor
description: When Skiff gets a crack in his hull, Thomas needs to move him overland to Harwick for repairs, but Skiff's land-sickness makes that challenging.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Tweety-Go-Round
description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

title: Business as Unusual
description: Bugs and Daffy open competing lemonade stands.

title: Potato
description: Bing and Sula find a potato with a nose on it in Amma's garden, and they want to keep it. So they call it Nosey. But, what will happen when they show Nosey how to go down the slide?

title: Race the Beast
description: Mush-Mush and his friends are determined to win the bark sledge race, but their essential fourth team member drops out. Our friends ask Mushpot to step up from being their coach to racing with them. The Mushelder is reluctant at first but soon reveals the tough competitor he is!

title: Band of Friends
description: Pocoyo meets a funny little red shape. At first it teases and hides from him, making him jump and chasing him around. But then it brings along its friends and together they put on a music and dancing show for Pocoyo and his gang.

title: Race Track Race
description: The Looney Builders race against the clock to build Cecil Turtle a new racetrack. Daffy gets caught up in his own desire to race and changes part of the build.

title: Picnic
description: It's picnic time! Bing and Flop are getting ready to have a picnic, but will they remember to bring everything they need?

title: A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream
description: The Baby Looney Tunes first Halloween involves a costume contest for Lola, Melissa and Petunia, group trick-or-treating and Sylvester overcoming his fear of confronting an allegedly scary neighbor.

title: Things That Go Plunk
description: A shy, puny member of the Bad Crowd shows up at the Cloudseeker claiming he's been kicked out of Blusterland for being nice. The Bears, leery at first, take him in despite Grumpy's suspicions that he is in cahoots with Bluster. It appears Grumpy is right - but thanks to the Care Bears, the little guy turns into a good friend with the courage to thwart Bluster's latest scheme.

title: An Alien Christmas Carol
description: The angry Martian hates Christmas since his father disappeared one Christmas Eve and he's decided to use his cannon to ruin Christmas for Pocoyo and his friends. But you never know what life has in store. After all, everyone has a heart.

title: Circus
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly are setting up a circus that will have acrobats, jugglers and clowns. The show begins. At first, the performers are not very coordinated, but in the end the performances are very entertaining and the audience has a great time.

title: Up Up and Away
description: Our friends are playing with a model airplane which shoots off up into space. They go on an adventure to retrieve the beloved toy, encountering some friendly, bendy aliens along the way.

title: Wide Load Vacay: Eye Spy
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, are traveling on the back of a truck from Montana to Utah. Charlie wants to play a game of Eye Spy. He finds more and more obvious objects for Frank to spy but Frank isn't quite getting the hang of it. Yet!

title: Riffle the Whiffle
description: The Bears encounter a lost Whiffle whose only word is "Riffle." They have no idea who he is or where he came from. Dibble is tasked with looking out for him until they learn where he lives. At first delighted to have a new playmate, she grows frustrated when he seems only to want to get away. With the aid of the Bears, Dibble helps solve the mystery of who he is and where he belongs.

title: Let Them Make Cake
description: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

title: Horse!
description: Pocoyo is flicking though a picture book when he sees something he's never seen before: a horse! He's amazed and obsessed. He desperately wants to have a horse. He searches everywhere and can talk of nothing but horses. His friends try to make a horse for him but Pocoyo rejects their attempt. Elly and Pato were only trying to help and now they're completely exasperated. Pocoyo is going mad - and driving them mad - just talking about horses all the time. Elly starts to cry in despair. Pocoyo realises that he's been driving them crazy and that they were only trying to help. He understands that there are no real horses in Pocoyo's world and he'll just have to do without. He plays with the pretend horse that Elly and Pato made and has loads of fun.

title: Musical Blocks
description: Pocoyo and Pato are having great fun playing with some magical blocks which form towers when music is played. But the fun turns to drama when Pato gets stuck on top of a high tower. How can Pocoyo return his ducky friend back to ground safely?

title: Ghost Camp/Boo/Never Boop a Robot
description: When Lucas and friends go camping, Avocado tells a scary story. Lucas now thinks there's a ghost in the garden./ Lucas loves to give his friends a scare on Halloween./ When Lucas boops a robot, he and his friends are chased around House!

title: A Secret Tweet
description: The babies plan a surprise birthday party for Tweety.

title: Mine
description: Bing and Pando are on their way home from the beach! And when Pando goes back to Bing's house to collect Bullabaloo, they decide to play one last game before bedtime - Hide and Seek. But where will Pando hide?

title: A Little Cloud
description: Pocoyo has an unusual new friend: a lonely little cloud who just wants to play.

title: Elly's New Doll
description: Elly's new doll has two arms, two legs and one head. Elly has to run an errand, so she leaves her doll with Pocoyo and Pato. When she returns, her doll is not in the same condition as when she left. Will they be able to put things right?

title: My Muddy Buddy
description: When Lilit creates a 'friends tree' mapping out who everyone is best friends with in Mushton, she realizes Muddler has no friends at all. Unable to accept this, Lilit slips away to try and befriend him. But Muddler's perception of friendship is somewhat unique, meaning Lilit now needs the help of her two best friends, Mush-Mush and Chep, to escape from Muddler's clutches.

title: Overnight Stop
description: Percy feels anxious about spending a night away from home during an overnight delivery with Thomas and Nia.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Time and Time Again
description: The babies learn the importance of telling time.

title: Robot Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo is transformed into a robot and tries to play with his friends, but all kinds of problems occur. How will this end?

title: Time After Time Before Time
description: Elly has been cooking her delicious cakes all day and now they're all ruined because of a banana skin. Don't panic! Nina has a plan! They'll travel back in time and stop the accident. What could go wrong?

title: Recycle Stomp
description: Mei, the children and some animals are in the park collecting trash to recycle!

title: Fussy Duck
description: Pato, fresh from his shower, is determined to keep clean. Pocoyo and Elly have very different ideas, and Pato soon realizes that half the fun of getting clean is getting dirty in the first place!

title: Bubbles
description: Bing and Pando are learning how to make bubbles, but will Bing be able to blow his own bubble?

title: The Harder They Fall
description: Bugs is embarrassed to admit he doesn't know how to skate.

title: Growing
description: Bing is having his height measured by Flop, but what will happen when Coco measures him again?

title: The Need for Feed/The Zipline Sisters of Treetop Woods
description: MacBarm is bringing food to his hungry chickens, that is, until all of the food falls out of his truck./Grandma and her twin sister want to recreate their old zipline act, but quickly discover that the zipline no longer exists!

title: Pirates
description: Pirate Pocoyo and Pato are duelling over a ship. Which one of them will manage to raise his pirate flag on it?

title: Share Your Care
description: Dibble plants the seeds of a strange bush outside of its natural environment, unaware that she has unleashed a disaster: The plant multiplies and begins to quickly spread. The Bears must find a way to stop its greedy growth before it crowds out all the other plants in the Silver Lining.

title: Are We There Yet?
description: Elly wants to make the most of the sun and decides to head off to the beach. Along the way, Elly sees her friends who all want to join her. With all the stopping, the trip drags on forever. And they don't even know how to get to the beach!

title: Kana Goes Slow
description: When Kana's power goes out during a delivery run, Thomas teaches her that sometimes it's okay to go slow.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Special Delivery
description: Chep knows so many things about nature that Mush-Mush and Lilit are confident he's not far from being an expert like Mushpot. So, when Travel Snail seems unwell, Mush-Mush and Lilit encourage their friend to take care of her in Mushpot's absence. Chep's diagnosis takes everyone by surprise: Travel Snail is expecting baby snails! At least that's what Chep is convinced about.

title: Snails Forever
description: Chep wants to return a favor to Mush-Mush, but all Mush-Mush wants is to have a compost pancake on Pancake Day! But when the Food Snail falls for, and takes off after, the Travel Snail, Pancake Day has to be cancelled. Chep sees an opportunity to save the day for his friend! But er, how do you solve a snail falling for another?

title: May the Best Taz Win
description: Lola learns she can't be the best at every sport.

title: Super Screen Cleaners
description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Pig Who Cried Woof
description: Petunia fakes emergencies. But when a real one arises, no one believes her.

title: Say What?
description: When Share magically has her voice stolen from her in a field of flowers, she and the other Bears must learn to listen so they can find her voice and solve the problem between the flowers and their Whiffle gardeners.

title: Out of the Cheer Zone
description: Two mischievous Whiffle kids come to play with Dibble, forcing Cheer to put her important work on hold to manage them. When she finds her "managing kids" skills lacking and her important work in jeopardy, she uses her skills as a leader to get the kids working as a team to help her complete her work while having fun at the same time.

title: The Littlest Tweety
description: Tweety is tired of being overlooked because of his diminutive size.

title: Bathing Loula
description: Loula has splashed about in a puddle, and now Pocoyo and Elly have to give her a bath. But Loula does not like taking a bath one bit and she keeps getting away. After several attempts, Loula is squeaky clean, but now someone else needs a bath.

title: Drum Roll Please
description: Pocoyo and his playmates love dancing to the Ball Orchestra's music. When it stops, they try to make their own band. Sleepy Bird's snoring sets the rhythm, and together they all make a wonderful, harmonious din.

title: Sandcastle
description: Blippi and TABBS go to the beach, where they meet Crabby the Crab! A local expert on sandcastles, Crabby teaches them how to build a castle that can't get washed away!

title: The Penguin Dance
description: Rico the penguin is visiting Lellobee city farm… and he's travelled all the way from the North pole!

title: Smoothie
description: It's snack time, but what will Bing and Flop make with the mushy banana?

title: Space Postal Service
description: Pato the Postman is back with a new mission: he has to deliver a package to the green Martian. But things aren't as simple as they seemed: the green Martian has moved to a different planet and Pato doesn't know his new address. You can do it, Pato!

title: Run, Mushpie, Run
description: Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit notice that Mushpie seems in great shape lately. They want to feel as great as she does and try to discover her secret. When they realise that she works out every morning, our friends decide to join her. And soon, all the Mushables do too. Now Lilit notices that Mushpie doesn't seem in such great shape anymore.

title: Present Tense
description: The Baby Looney Tunes pitch in to make an Arbor Day gift for Granny while Baby Lola, who suggested they do so, tries to make Granny a present on her own.

title: Fetch Loula Fetch!
description: Pocoyo and Loula are going to the beach, but they keep losing their ball. They learn about colors, shapes and sizes as they meet their friends along the way.

title: Let's Get Rolling!/A Bit of a Stretch!
description: It's MacBarm's croquet tournament and Zee made giant decorations but they're too big to get to the farm./It's the opening day of the skyscraper and the Mechas need to put the sphere on top of the building before the ribbon cutting ceremony.

title: The Seed
description: Pocoyo finds a seed. He can't wait for it to grow. He guards it lovingly but can't prevent his friends from taking an interest in the seed too. Sleepy Bird thinks it would make a tasty snack but Pocoyo stops her from munching it just in time. Loula thinks it's a toy to bury and Pato thinks it's an egg. Finally Pocoyo erects a comprehensive security system to protect his seed but Elly accidentally knocks it over. Pocoyo's seed grows into a beautiful flower. But Loula picks it and shakes it. Pocoyo is upset until he realizes - -with our help - that Loula's shaking of the flower has simply made more seeds fall on the ground, and therefore more beautiful flowers have grown.

title: Bye Bye Bee/Jeepers Peepers/House is Breathing
description: Saying goodbye can be hard, but there are ways to feel close to your friends./ Can Dimples finally beat Weebscuit at a staring competition?/ Lucas is convinced House is alive when the heating vent comes on.

title: Pocoyo and Nina's Terror Show
description: Pocoyo and Nina put on a puppet show for their friends. They can't wait to see their scared faces... But they don`t get scared at all, the show is hilarious!

title: Noise to My Ears
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird have great fun making lots of noise. But what's music to their ears is a real old racket to poor Pato who's trying to have a nap. Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird agree to try to be more considerate. But then they find another wonderful way to make music - by bouncing balls. Again, their music wakes up the sleepy duck. Finally Pocoyo and his chums make a cacophony with lots of machines. Pato completely loses his cool. Pocoyo's attempt at a soothing lullaby does nothing to calm the ever-more exhausted quacker. Pato realizes there's no other way round this - he's going to have to conduct them himself. In so doing, he really gets into it and the music gives him lots of energy. He's no longer sleepy and everyone's playing brilliant harmonious music together.

title: Popsicle
description: Blippi shrinks down and goes on a sweet and exciting adventure through an ice cream truck with Sherry Pop, a fruit popsicle, finding out that she and all frozen treats need to be in the ice-cold so they won't melt.

title: Bake
description: Bing and Flop are baking Ginger Bunny cookies in the oven for Coco and Charlie. Will Chickie Timer ring to tell them it's time to come out of the oven?

title: Elly's Ballet Class
description: Elly wants to be a prima ballerina with a troupe of other dancers so she tries to teach her friends to dance just like her. But she gets frustrated that they can't do it straight away and is very bossy. Finally everyone dances together in their own special way.

title: Hippoty Hoppity Voosh
description: Voooooosh! Bing and Sula are vooshing Hoppity and Fairy Hippo up higher and higher. What will happen when Fairy Hippo flies up a little too high and doesn't come back down again?

title: Sir Topham Hatt's Hat
description: When Sir Topham Hatt's Hat blows away in the wind before making an important announcement, Thomas and his friends race around Sodor, trying to catch it. The Hat remains out of reach until they learn to work together.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Rusty Rescue
description: When Thomas throws away Diesel's favorite oil can thinking it's trash, he makes a promise to get it back and learns it's better not to touch things that aren't yours.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Mural
description: Sula and Amma are painting a mural when Bing and Flop arrive and help. Amma reminds Bing that when painting, it's important to remember to "Dip it... and... Wipe it" to stop the drips! But what will happen when Bing forgets to wipe his brush?

title: Move It!
description: Overhearing Granny making a call to Manny the Mover, Baby Bugs and Baby Lola jump to the conclusion they're all moving away from Granny's house.

title: Storytime
description: It's bath time and Bing's reading his favourite story. When the book falls in the bath, how will Bing read the story?

title: A Hole in One!
description: Elly is playing golf. She positions herself to hit the ball. She aims at the flag, hits the ball with the golf club and it lands in the hole. Good shot! Pocoyo tries to imitate her, but since he does not know how to play, he cheats in order to beat Elly. Elly gets angry with him, but in the end, she teaches him to play without cheating.

title: The Hero Trap
description: The Mushlets love Mush-Mush's heroic stories. But when they demand to see him actually do something heroic, Mush-Mush feels he can't back out - and so ends up stuck up a cliff. Relieved to be rescued by Chep and Lilit, Mush-Mush is about to admit that he isn't a hero when the Mushlets find themselves in danger. Now Mush-Mush has no choice but to be a real hero!

title: Puppy Love
description: Pocoyo neglects Loula when he finds a toy dog to play with.

title: A Light Delivery
description: When Thomas accidentally breaks a light he's hauling to the Sodor Festival of Lights, he learns the best way to be the #1 engine is to be honest when you make a mistake.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Dragon Run
description: Thomas has the honor of pulling the dragon to the Medieval Faire, but everyone wants a turn as well.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Wheels on the Bus
description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

title: Nia's Perfect Plan
description: Nia has volunteered for a big day of deliveries and is determined to make the perfect plan to get it done, but when things start to go awry, she doggedly sticks to her plan and refuses any help.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Silence Challenge
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly challenge Narrator to spend some time without talking. Will he be able to do it?

title: New Cat in Town
description: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving.

title: Pocoyo's Restaurant
description: Pocoyo and Elly have set up a restaurant. They have everything: tables, chairs, plates, cups, silverware and so on. Their first guest is a hungry Martian in a bad mood. Thanks to their efforts, he is satisfied when he leaves. But an interesting surprise awaits them.

title: Tourist Trapped
description: A group of green Martians have come to Pocoyo World to take photos of our friends. The tourists keep flocking to see them, will it ever stop? They're everywhere. Even in the fridge!

title: Table for Fun
description: When Pocoyo and Elly decide to play restaurants, a very hungry Pato becomes their unwilling and unwitting guest. But Pato doesn't understand that it's a game.

title: Halloween Potion
description: It's Halloween and Pocoyo and friends are very excited to go trick-or-treating! Witch Elly is preparing a delicious cream to enjoy before they set out scaring. With full bellies and sure that they are the scariest, they get ready for an evening of fun… but they soon discover that there is a clear winner, it seems that a real monster is loose…! Or maybe not…? Halloween is a magical night and anything is possible!

title: The Rescue
description: Pocoyo and friends must rescue Caterpillar from the top of a tree, so they come up with plenty of crazy plans. Will they succeed?

title: Comfort Level
description: Sylvester learns to live without his blankey.

title: Ice Creamed
description: It's Taz's birthday, so The Looney Builders build him a huge ice cream sundae. Porky worries about making a mistake and delays the build causing the ice cream to start to melt.

title: Nia's Surprising Surprise
description: Nia is planning a big party to celebrate the anniversary of her arrival on Sodor, but she finds that her friends don't remember her anniversary and are too busy to even talk about it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Say Goodbye
description: Bing and Sula are having so much fun playing together, they don't want to say goodbye. What will happen when Amma comes to collect Sula?

title: Puddle Olympics
description: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

title: Pato's Shower
description: Pato has his towel, soap and brush ready for a shower when the phone rings. He goes to answer the phone and when he returns all of his things have disappeared. Pato starts searching and finds that his friends are playing with them. At the end of the episode Pocoyo and Elly realize that it wasn't nice to take Pato's things without permission and help to make Pato's shower unforgettable.

title: More Cowbell
description: Thomas is elated when he finds a cowbell on the side of the tracks, until his friends start hogging it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: One Wise Bear
description: The Bears become lost in the Valley of Whispering Winds, where voices whisper in their ears and make them lose faith in themselves. Racing to their rescue, Tenderheart leads them to the only one who knows the antidote to the words of the Winds: a mysterious old bear of great wisdom who teaches them a valuable lesson about listening to your heart.

title: Picnic Puzzle
description: Pocoyo and Elly have organized a picnic and they leave Pato in charge of guarding the sandwiches while they get everything ready. Incredibly the sandwiches suddenly start moving around. Pato can't believe his eyes. When Pocoyo and Elly return they are angry with Pato. They think he took the sandwiches himself. They give him one more chance, leaving him in charge of guarding the cake. Once again, amazingly, the cake runs away apparently on its own. Pato is once again berated by Pocoyo and Elly until they see what's going on with their own eyes. Pocoyo investigates further and discovers who it is that's moving the food around: ANTS! Having worked out what's going on, the friends invite the ants along to the picnic and they all have fun together.

title: Come On Charlie
description: Charlie is coming! And Bing has planned lots of games to play with him. But what happens when Charlie doesn't want to play any of the games Bing has put out?

title: Acorns
description: Bing and Sula are collecting and counting acorns in the Howly Woods. But when they start to disappear, Flop explains that they need to stay mousy quiet to find out where they're going!

title: Baby Bird Sitting
description: When Sleepy Bird has to pop out for a while, she needs someone to look after little Baby Bird. Pato volunteers because he thinks that's going to be a much easier job than tidying up the mess he's made with Pocoyo. Baby Bird, and his chum Caterpillar, run rings round Pato who eventually appeals to Pocoyo for help. Pocoyo thinks he can take care of the situation easily himself, but he similarly is foxed by the little tykes. Finally Pocoyo and Pato work out that in order to get the little ones to do what they want, they are going to need to collaborate. By the time Sleepy Bird returns, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are fast asleep. Little does Sleepy Bird know the chaos that got them to that point!

title: Mr. McStuffles
description: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it.

title: Twinkle Twinkle
description: Elly finds a beautiful star that has fallen out of the night sky. She loves it and wants to keep it for herself. But Pocoyo makes her realize that the star is for everyone to enjoy. Together they put it back where it's meant to be.

title: All Washed Up
description: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath.

title: To Tell the Tooth
description: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

title: Elly's Market
description: Elly has set up a market to play with her friends. She has oranges, apples and bananas. Pocoyo and Pato are having fun playing with the fruit stand and they break it. They have to fix it and put each fruit back in its place.

title: I Don't Want to go to Sleep
description: It's time for bed, but Pocoyo is not sleepy, he just wants to play! But, while playing with the blocks or the ball he seems to nod off a little bit… or maybe not? Pocoyo shakes his head to wake up and continues playing… even with his eyes closed. Will he fall asleep?

title: Puppy Love/ House Grand Prix/ Farewell Sweet Ride
description: Avocado's friends take her on her daily walkies. / Lucas and Findley race around House to determine who is the fastest out of their element. /Bodhi processes the loss of her favorite snowboard.

title: Mad Mix Machine
description: Pocoyo finds a super duper machine that mixes objects and makes special new toys to play with. But when Pocoyo puts his friends' toys in the machine for fun, he upsets them. Eventually Pocoyo has to put things back to normal and then share his new magic machine with his friends so they can all enjoy it.

title: My Hero
description: After being rescued by him, Caterpillar decides to "help" Pocoyo win his golf match against Pato. Will she get him in trouble?

title: A New View for Thomas
description: When Thomas spends the day carrying rockstar idol Harold across Sodor, he gains a new perspective on just how amazing it is to be his engine-self.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Woof
description: Bing and Flop are in the park, when a doggie called Sunshine comes to play catch with them! Bing loves playing with Sunshine, but what will happen when Bing realises he can't keep Sunshine?

title: Bat and Ball
description: It's time for a game of Bat and Ball with Octopus. Everyone wants to have a turn at batting, but the friends learn that you have to wait your turn.

title: The Messy Guest
description: Pocoyo is having a lovely time playing with his friends but little does he realize that he's making a mess and leaving them to clear it all up! When he sees that his friends no longer want to play with him, he comes to understand the importance not only of having fun and making a mess, but of helping and clearing up too.

title: The Whatsacallit of Treetop Woods/Nat in the Dark!
description: Berta is opening an exhibit on the Whatsacallit of Treetop Woods. If only she could get a picture to prove it's real./Gerry and Nat are leading the Treetop Troops on a hike, but Nat finds himself lost in the woods as it gets darker.

title: A Surprise for Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo's friends decide to give him a surprise party - simply to show him how much they love him.

title: The Birthday That Wasn't
description: Dibble misunderstands the Bears' intentions when they secretly make a plush toy Whiffle for her "Un-birthday." Thinking it's real and that the Bears love it more than they love her, she steals it and plans to leave it in the forest. She has second thoughts and returns her "rival" to her friends, only to learn that it's a gift to show their love for her.

title: Duck Stuck
description: Pocoyo finds a strange door. When he opens it, it seems to lead to the sky. Every time Pocoyo opens the door it seems to open up somewhere new.

title: Taz in Toyland
description: After Taz breaks all of his toys, Granny gives him one last chance to care for something.

title: Lost in Space
description: Pocoyo goes to visit his alien friend who wants to show him around his beautiful planet. Pocoyo and the alien have so much fun with the new things that they see and hear that soon they don't know where they are. At first they both panic but Pocoyo realizes with the narrator's and viewers' help that if he tries to remember the last place he was he'll be sure to find his way home.

title: The Badge of Courage
description: When Dibble dresses up as a superhero complete with a pretend belly badge, the Whiffles think she's the real thing and need her to confront an imaginary monster that they believe lives in a cave. She bravely enters the cave but loses her courage when she loses the belly badge, until Funshine convinces her that her bravery came from inside her.

title: The Wheel Deal
description: Everyone's excited about a grand bicycle outing through the park, everyone except Tweety whose little legs don't quite reach the pedals. Frustrated after riding on the back of Floyd's bicycle while everyone else has fun, Tweety is ready to go home.

title: Rules of the Game
description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Down on the Farm
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Pato are in the garden, where they have planted tomatoes, carrots and lettuce. When it is time to pick and eat them, the vegetables suddenly start to move by themselves. They finally catch them and discover why they were moving.

title: Detective Pocoyo
description: Elly is aghast to realize that her darling doll is missing. Detective Pocoyo decides to help Elly and he looks for clues as to where her doll might be. While Pocoyo goes back to the scene of the crime, Elly finds that she had her doll all along: it wasn't lost at all, she'd simply mislaid it. Elly is too embarrassed to own up and tells Pocoyo she doesn't need her doll anymore. But Detective Pocoyo uncovers the truth and the mystery is solved.

title: Tell-A-Photo
description: As Granny assembles her photo album, the babies gather around to reminisce about all the happy times they've spent together.

title: Baa Baa Black Sheep
description: It's getting chilly on the farm! Summers dwindled into autumn and everyone is in need of some winter clothing

title: Valley of the Shamrocks
description: When Grumpy replaces mission navigator Good Luck with a computerized navigational gadget, Good Luck feels useless -- until he saves the Valley of the Shamrocks and is proclaimed a hero by the Whiffles, who don't want him to leave. He is torn between staying with the Whiffles and remaining with the Bears.

title: War of the Weirds
description: Marvin the Martian comes to visit, and the babies learn to accept differences.

title: I'll Do it in a Minute/Cloud Gazing/Don't Do That Arlo
description: Arlo has fun playing, but he procrastinates when it comes to tidying up./ Lucas, Arlo, and Findley have a day of make-believe with the clouds./ Arlo can't resist the temptation to look into next door's garden through a knothole.

title: Star Helpers
description: Starmush's back is stuck, and the Mushelder has no choice but to ask for help in Mushton. Because Chep is the one that finds a solution to his back problem, Starmush chooses him to help with his daily activities. But Mush-Mush is jealous, he would have loved being the chosen one…

title: Everyone's Present
description: Wow… Presents! One for Pocoyo, one for Elly and one for Pato! How exciting. Pocoyo's present is some string, Pato gets some paper and Elly some sticks. They have fun for a while, each playing with their own present in a bid to prove that it's the best of the bunch. But ultimately the friends get a little bored with their respective gifts. After all, there's only so much you can do with one thing. In a huff, the friends throw their new toys on the floor. And this is when they see the potential of the presents: they can combine them. They put the presents together to make a kite. Wonderful, something they can all play with together.

title: Here I Go
description: Bing and Pando find a new slide at the playground, but it's very high. Will Bing be able to go down the slide?

title: Old Macdonald
description: Rishi goes around the farm with Ella, organising all the animals so they can have a soccer game!

title: The Remote Control
description: Pocoyo discovers that the TV remote allows him to change, mute and rewind his friends. He will never again have to argue about what channel to watch! This is great. Or perhaps not…?

title: Christmas Tree
description: It's Christmas time and Pato wants to decorate a Christmas tree. He can't bring himself to fell an innocent fern, but with a bit of ingenuity and a lot of team work the gang manages to find the perfect tree. Merry Christmas!

title: The Show Must Go On
description: Mushpie loves to sing. The only problem is she is terrible at it! But Lilit, who has never heard her sing before, wants to make Mushpie happy and organizes a concert for her to sing in front of all the other Mushables… who are terrified at the idea! But Lilit doesn't have the heart to admit this to Mushpie.

title: Firehouse Frolics
description: The Baby Looney Tunes tour the local fire station, learning fire prevention tips from friendly Fireman Frank. Later, Baby Daffy, the most reluctant and uninterested participant, displays the most fire-fighting knowledge when he is suddenly tested by a real-life emergency at Granny's house.

title: Sorry Not Sorry
description: While observing an ancient Whiffle ritual, Grumpy accidentally steps on a sentient plant. When his apology sends the plant and Whiffles into an upset, Share helps him learn how to genuinely apologize from his heart, and that a real apology is about how the other person feels, not about yourself.

title: Can-Do Submarine Crew
description: Thomas and Percy think they're great communicators, but when they're tasked with delivering a submarine to Vicarstown, communication becomes a bit more difficult… to say the least!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Pocoyo's Present
description: Pocoyo has a beautifully wrapped up present but he won't open it. Elly is dying to know what's inside. She begs and pleads but when that fails she turns to desperate measures.

title: Wise Quacker
description: Melissa gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but she takes the jokes too far.

title: License to Deliver
description: When Percy has to deliver a new light bulb to the lighthouse at night, Thomas suggests playing secret agents along the way to help Percy forget about his fear of the dark.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Quiet Delivery
description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Bird Call
description: Chanterelle has built a whistle that can reproduce the most beautiful sound of the forest: the one of the Nightingale. When the whistle disappears, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit soon discover that it has been stolen by a beetle. In order to finally hear what a real Nightingale sounds like, they'll have to get it back!

title: The Big Whifflesnooze
description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

title: Show
description: Bing and his friends are at the bandstand in the park when they all decide to put on a show! And Bing's singing the Rainybow song for the finale! But what will happen when Bing doesn't like everybody looking at him?

title: Shake the Apple Tree
description: It's the end of the summer and the trees are full of delicious apples ready to be picked!

title: Pato's Living Room
